title: zucchini delicious
directions: Chop bacon and fry slightly.
Add onion and cook until golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Cook until tender on low (electric skillet 2).
Most of the sauce will be absorbed. Cooking time 20 - 25 minutes.

title: oven fried sesame chicken
directions: Combine sesame seed, flour and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in soy sauce and dredge in sesame seed mixture. Arrange chicken in baking dish. Drizzle melted margarine over chicken. Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains about 221 calories per serving.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Cut seed out of zucchini.
Peel and grate 1/2 gallon.
Mix grated zucchini and other ingredients.
Heat to a boil and then simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack in pint jars.
Pressure cook for 5 minutes at 5 pounds of pressure.

title: peanut pretzel brittle
directions: Melt chocolate until creamy in double boiler.
While chocolate is warm, mix in pretzel pieces and peanuts (easy).
Spread thin on cookie sheet.
When cool, break in pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a thread, then add peanuts. Cook until peanuts seem to pop and syrup mixture is a light brown. Take off the stove. Add soda, mixing well. Pour into Pam sprayed pie plates.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Brown the ground beef.
In a baking dish, place one layer of tortillas, dipped in enchilada sauce.
Put a thin layer of ground beef on top of tortillas.
Take more tortillas dipped in enchilada sauce and place them on top of the beef.
Alternate these layers until meat and tortillas fill pan.
Sprinkle cheese on the top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Place remaining ingredients on top of enchiladas when ready to serve.

title: make ahead brunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half of the bread slices evenly over the bottom, cutting off crusts and using crusts to fill in the empty spaces.
Layer shredded cheese over the bread and top with a second layer of bread.
Mix together 8 eggs and 1/3 cup milk.
Beat until well blended.
Pour over bread in pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snow peak icing
directions: Place flour and milk in small pan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly,
or until a thickened paste.
Cool for 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Transfer to small electric mixer bowl. Add margarine, Crisco and sugar to bowl.
Mix on medium to high mixer speed until light and fluffy.
Will ice an 8 or 9-inch layer cake.
Quite different.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box; let cool.
Mix pudding per directions.
In large punch bowl, crumble cake.
Put 1/2 in bottom of bowl.
Spread half of pudding over cake.
Add half of other ingredients in order given.
Layer one at a time.
Add remaining cake; repeat layers.
End with Cool Whip and garnish top with cherries.
Makes beautiful centerpiece during holidays.

title: pull apart mexican cornbread
directions: Cook green peppers and onions in little water until tender. Mix all ingredients together; add butter last.
Place in a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: brownie mix
directions: Stir just until blended; spread in 8 x 8-inch pan (greased). Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter surprise
directions: Mix all together.
Use 9 x 13 pan.
Break in pieces peanut butter cookies, Nutter butter or Keebler double peanut butter cookies.
Put layer of cookies in pan first, then your pudding, Cool Whip, etc., next, then another layer of cookies on top.

title: holt's sausage soup(serves 4)
directions: Prepare vegetables.
Peel and chop onions coarsely.
Trim white part of leeks and wash under cold water; slice thin.
Peel and mince garlic.
Pare and cut turnips and potatoes into 1/2-inch dice.
Wash and thickly slice mushrooms.
Pare and cut carrots into 1/4-inch slices.
Trim, wash and tear spinach into 2-inch pieces.
Saute onions, leeks and garlic in butter for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add turnips, potatoes, mushrooms and carrots; cook 3 minutes.
Add stock; heat to boiling, then simmer, covered, 8 to 10 minutes.
Add spinach, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Saute kielbasa in oil until brown.
Remove and drain; add to soup.
Serve with sprinkle of parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Brown patties; put in baking dish and pour Heinz brown gravy mix over.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: deer chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add rest of ingredients to taste.
Don't add water; it gets soupy as it cooks.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: drunk chicken
directions: Saute onions
in
oleo.
Brown chicken.
Add the soups. Rinse can with water and use the water.
Cook 45 minutes.
Add 1 cup cooking
wine.
Let
simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
(This gravy is real good over cooked rice.)

title: louisiana red beans and rice
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
Mix all ingredients and place in crock pot.
Cook on low for 6-8 hours.
In the last hour, add rice.
Be sure to stir occasionally.
I usually do this on the weekends or when I know I am going to be around to check on it.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa.
Add to milk, which has come to the boiling point.
Then add Karo syrup and cook until it forms a soft ball in water.
Beat well.
Drop by teaspoons on a piece of foil.

title: marie cann casserole
directions: Mix together and set overnight to chill. Bake in a 9 x 13 pan. Cover top with bread crumbs. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all the above ingredients and bake in 9x13 dish at 350° for 4 hours uncovered.
Serves 10-12.

title: cheesy au gratin potatoes
directions: Defrost and drain potatoes.
Combine potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole with onions, soup, cheese and sour cream.
Mix well.
Melt margarine and drip over top.
Spread crumbled potato chips over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: snow cake
directions: Tear cake into small pieces.
Put 1/2 in bottom of pan. Dissolve gelatine in hot water.
Add cold water and sugar.
Let thicken in refrigerator until consistency of egg whites.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple; mix well.
Spread half of cake, another layer of cake and rest of mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
I add pecans, coconut, etc.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Pour in Ragu and let simmer. Cook lasagna noodles until tender.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer hamburger-Ragu sauce over noodles, then 2 cups of cheese on 3 layers cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Reserve broth.
Pull meat off bones in small pieces.
Line bottom of baking dish with chicken.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dry stuffing mix on top.
Pour enough chicken broth to cover entire casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in casserole.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add flour; add milk.
Stir until thick.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour white sauce over potatoes; mix well.
Add onion, caraway seed and cheese.
Mix well. Bake uncovered at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill 5 quart crock-pot to top with peeled, chopped apples.
Add 1/2 cup water or less.
Cook 18 to 24 hours, stirring occasionally. Add cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Cook 3 more hours to desired thickness.
Fill jars and seal.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Beat together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour mix to egg mix. Fold in apples and pecans. Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Better if baked 2 hours. Test with toothpick. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frying pan.
Salt and pepper to taste; drain.
Add catsup, water and sugar.
Mix well, then add macaroni.
Stir and let simmer until done.

title: perfect fudge every time
directions: Pour first 2 ingredients into microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Continue to microwave at 30 second intervals until chips have started to melt.
Once chips start to melt, stir until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Add vanilla; stir well.
Pour fudge into an 8-inch square pan lined with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until firm; cut into 1-inch squares.

title: spinach dip
directions: Boil eggs 10 minutes.
Pour off hot water, run under cold water.
Peel and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove yolk, set aside whites.

title: harvest soup
directions: In large, heavy pot, "sweat" onion, covered, over low heat, until soft.
Stir in squash, apples and 3 cups of chicken broth. Cook, covered, over low heat until squash and apples are soft. Remove from heat.
Puree in small batches in food processor or blender.
Return to pot.
Add the 1 pint half and half.
Add additional chicken broth if necessary to achieve consistency of thick cream soup.
Season with honey, herbs and pepper.
Simmer on low.
Combine sour cream and brandy.
Ladle soup into bowls and garnish with brandy, sour cream and parsley sprigs.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Open all cans and drain juice in medium size bowl.
Put fruit in large bowl.
Mix pudding with fruit juice.
Pour fruit juice and pudding mixture over fruit and mix.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Put one can soup in crock-pot first, then add chicken.
Season to taste with seasoning salt.
Then put the other can of soup on the chicken, top with mushrooms.
Put paprika to taste.

title: machuca(plantain and fish soup)
directions: Combine water and coconut mixture to make soup.
(Be sure to strain the ground coconut and water mix.)
Combine above ingredients into coconut milk mixture in a large pot.
Peel and boil plantains in a large pot that will hold all the ingredients together after boiling.
Once plantain are tender, mash like mashed potatoes, then set aside.
If you are using fish in this recipe, let fish cook in coconut milk mixture soup until tender. Serve hot.
Use large soup bowls to serve.
The mashed plantain are dipped into soup.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving small amount of cheese to sprinkle on top.
Pour into greased casserole or quiche dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
This doesn't last long!

title: relish
directions: Whack up vegetables ('ceptin' celery), grate cabbage 'n let soak in salt watah overnite...git up nex mawnin' 'n squeez salt watah outta vegtubles by hand...now put mixture in hot vinegar wid the sugah 'n drop in spices (what you've got tied up in a cloth)...Let the mess cum to a boil 'n drop cut up celery in.

title: tricks
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts and chocolate chips.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and cook 1 hour in unbaked crust at 350°.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large pot.
Add to pot the peppers, onions and cauliflower which have been chopped (not fine).
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Put in jars and seal.

title: award winning soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour and baking soda, set aside. In a large bowl, cream together the butter, brown sugar, and white sugar. Beat in the instant pudding mix until blended. Stir in the eggs and vanilla. Blend in the flour mixture. Finally, stir in chocolate chips or chunks and nuts. Drop cookies by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in the preheated oven. Edges should be golden brown.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water, about 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream, stir in carrots and fold in squash and onions.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Roll ball in crushed nuts.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all together and spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: hearty ham casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first four ingredient; set aside.
In a sauce pan, saute onion in butter for 2 minutes, stir in flour until blended.
Gradually add milk and pepper.
Bring to a boil, cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; pour over the ham mixture and stir until combined.
Transfer to a greased 11 x 7 x 2 inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until the cheese is melted.

title: recipe for a good cook
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose when too young. When once selected, give entire thought to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping a husband in a pickle, others are constantly getting one in hot water.
This makes him sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even a poor variety may be made sweet, tender, and good by garnishing him with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
Wrap one in a mantle of charity and keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, one will keep for years.

title: anadama bread
directions: Stir cornmeal very slowly into boiling water. When thoroughly mixed, add shortening, molasses and salt. Cool. When lukewarm, add yeast and flour (enough to make a stiff dough). Knead well. Keep in warm place. Let rise to more than double in bulk. Shape into 2 loaves. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 1 hour.

title: hershey layer cake
directions: Melt Hershey bar in top of double boiler over hot water.
Cool. Cream margarine with sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9-inch square cake pans in 350° preheated oven for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost cake with your favorite frosting.

title: pork shu mai
directions: Blend all filling ingredients together and mix well.
Place about 2 teaspoons of filling in the center of a wrapper.
Cup the skin around the filling and gently pleat the upper parts of the wrapper around the exposed filling.

Garnish the exposed filling with a pea, slice of mushroom and a pinch of colored powdered fish (other garnishings may be used). Steam the Shu Mai on a grated plate for about 25 minutes. Serve hot with soy sauce and red vinegar.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix and allow to marinate.
Chill and serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix chilled, cooked pasta with all veggies and diced eggs. Mix Miracle whip with spices, juice, salt and pepper.
Mix dressing and salad.
Serve cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg with fork and stir in milk and oil. Mix dry ingredients. Stir together with egg mixture just until flour is moistened. Batter will be lumpy. Stir in blueberries. Bake in greased muffin cups 20 to 25 minutes at 400°. Makes 12 muffins.

title: blackberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In large bowl, combine berries, sugar and lemon juice together with 2 tablespoons flour. Pour into deep-dish pie plate. In separate bowl, blend remaining 1/2 cup flour, brown sugar and butter. Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over berries. Bake for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: mama's candied yams
directions: Peel
potatoes, then wash and dry them.
Slice potatoes thick, about 1/4-inch, longwise.
Sprinkle with lemon juice so they don't
turn
dark.	Put
butter
in heavy skillet.	Melt until just hot.
Turn heat on low or medium-low (according to stove;
I use low).
Turn frequently, but carefully, and cook until tender. It takes about 1 hour.
Put sugar in as soon as you put potatoes in.
Also add cinnamon (just sprinkle about 2 teaspoons).
Turn carefully or they will come apart.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Combine jellies in saucepan.
Add mustard and heat until dissolved.
Add hot dogs and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together the last 5 ingredients; bring to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator a couple of weeks.

title: sundae brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously prick bottom and sides of pie crust with fork.
Bake crust 10 minutes; remove from oven. Meanwhile, in large bowl, beat eggs; stir in sugar and butter. Stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and nuts.
Pour into pie crust.
Return to oven.
Bake additional 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set.
(Pie will not test done in center.)
Serve warm or cool with ice cream; drizzle with topping.
Garnish with Kiss.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Core and cut apples, but
do not peel.	Add only enough water to cook apples
until
soft.
Press through colander and measure. Combine all ingredients
in
a turkey roaster.
Cook in oven at 325° for about
to
hours,
stirring every 30 minutes.
Pour into sterilized
jars
to
within 1/2-inch from top.
Put
on cap.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Yields 9 pints.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Open biscuits, one can at a time, coating biscuits well with cinnamon and sugar mixture so the biscuits won't stick together. Cut the biscuits into quarters and put pieces into the Bundt pan.
Pour the melted butter over the biscuit pieces, then bake for 30 minutes.

title: quick yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a small bowl.
In a large bowl cream sugar with melted margarine.
Add egg and yeast mixture. Stir in flour until well mixed.
Place dough in airtight container, not filling more than 2/3 full.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before baking.

title: hidden valley ranch fiesta dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Make day ahead of time. Serve with taco chips.

title: pork diane skillet supper
directions: Melt margarine in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork slices.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until browned on both sides. Remove pork from skillet; set aside.
Reserve 1/4 cup broth.
Add remaining broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and potatoes to skillet.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add mushrooms, onions and pork.
Cover; simmer 5 more minutes.
In small bowl combine flour and broth.
Stir, then add to pork mixture.
Cook until bubbly and thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: cool summer salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Dice tomato, onions and red onion. Slice, mix and add olives.
After seasoning, pour over Italian dressing.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: side line potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spiced sesame bars
directions: Beat egg.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Stir in butter. Sift in dry ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/2 seeds in bottom of greased 8-inch square pan.
Pour in batter and top with remaining seeds. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cocoa roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil or waxed paper and grease paper.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, beat eggs 5 minutes, until thickened and lemon colored. Pour eggs into large mixing bowl; beat in granulated sugar.
On low speed, blend in water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating just until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan, spreading batter to corners.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: layered diablo dip
directions: Ingredients are layered in circles on a large round plate or platter.
The size of each succeeding layer is gradually decreased, so as to build Mt. Diablo.
Form the bottom and largest circle with avocados.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning; spread on avocados.
Layer both cheeses and pat down.
Next, tomatoes and black olives.
Top with onion.
Serves 12 or 14.
(Double recipe to feed moderate to large crowd.)

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients. Form and shape mixture into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients well and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top near the end of baking.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake tested with knife comes out clean.

title: shrimp and garlic with pasta
directions: Saute garlic in oil until soft.
Do not burn.
Add basil and parsley.
Stir in broth.
Bring to boil; reduce to simmer.
Add shrimp and cover.
Cook for approximately 10 minutes until shrimp is done.
Add dash of pepper, squeeze fresh lemon.
Add cooked pasta; stir and serve.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: After baking potatoes in oven or microwave, cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center.
Mash potatoes.
Add 4 ounces of cheese and remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture back in shells. Sprinkle with 4 ounces of shredded cheese.
Bake for additional 20 to 25 minutes.

title: betty's meat balls
directions: In large bowl blend ingredients.
Roll into balls any size you please.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain.
They freeze very well.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix hamburger, onion, salt and pepper together.
Shape into balls.
Place in baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over meatballs.
Bake for about 25 minutes.

title: baked bean quintet
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove; reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Drain and crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in reserved drippings until tender but not brown; drain.
In a large bowl, combine bacon, onion, garlic, butter beans, pork and beans, kidney beans, garbanzo beans and lima beans.
Mix catsup, molasses, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, prepared mustard and pepper.
Mix with bean mixture.
Turn into 2 1/2-quart bean pot or casserole.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until heated through.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: poppy seed cheese bread
directions: Mix bisquick, cheese, egg and milk.
Beat one minutes.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients reserving half of the bread crumbs for topping.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top and bake.
Serves 6.

title: soup for friends(dedicated to mary and jessie)
directions: Blend ingredients and cook for 45 minutes (or longer), bringing to a boil, then simmer.

title: chicken breast marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and let chicken marinate 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Combine with crab mixture.
Crumble some saltines.
Shape cakes and roll in crumbled crackers.
Fry in a little margarine until a nice brown.
Enjoy!

title: grandma's cobbler
directions: Place fruit in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and dot with butter or margarine.
Heat in a 350° oven while mixing batter.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening.
Stir in combined egg and milk.
Spoon over hot fruit.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes (until firm to touch).
Cool.

title: ruth's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 3 to 5 minutes. Start counting when mixture has reached a full boiling (rolling boil).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, oatmeal, peanut butter, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello first.
Then add other ingredients and mix by hand.
Needs to sit in refrigerator for an hour or so before serving.

title: "snowball" cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand and roll into little balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown and roll in 10x sugar while warm.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine in a 2-quart pan, the sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine; bring to a full boil for about 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: yummy dip
directions: Mix together until creamy.
Spread on celery sticks or serve in bowl as a dip.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onions and salt; let stand overnight.
In morning drain and rinse well.
Mix remaining ingredients with zucchini.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: microwave swedish meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup milk, onion, parsley, salt, allspice and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs (about 30) and arrange in a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Cook on Medium-high for 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes.
Push meatballs to one side of dish.
Blend in soup and remaining milk; combine with meatballs.
Cook, covered with plastic wrap, at Medium-high 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve with buttered noodles.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: donna's dessert
directions: Crust:
Melt butter/margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add flour and chopped pecans.
Combine to form dough and pat into bottom of pan.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Remove and let cool.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Mix equal parts of juice and ginger ale in a punch bowl.
Make ice ring using punch mixture.
Freeze and float in punch.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in casserole and cover with Tater Tots (frozen).
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot seafood dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown beef and onions.
When browned, add the remaining ingredients and let cook for about 1 1/2 hours.
Drain off excess fat.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all well and pour into unbaked crust and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Coarsely grind pears and mix with salt, sugar, and celery seed in a pot. Make paste of remaining dry ingredients and 1 c. vinegar in another pot and cook a few minutes. Add rest of vinegar and ground ingredients. Cook 15 minutes. Seal in pint jars while hot. Makes 10 pt.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes after margarine melts.
Refrigerate.
Use on anything you like with sauce.
Very tasty on meat or fried chicken.

title: shoney's original strawberry pie
directions: Heat 7-Up with cornstarch.
Add Jell-O and sugar.
Simmer and stir until slightly thick; let cool.
Bake pie shell and cool. Pour into shell the strawberries.
Pour Jell-O mixture over berries.
Refrigerate until thick.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients and pour into unbaked pastry shell. Put top pastry on, seal edges and make 4 slits evenly spaced on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until brown.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 8-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° until done.
It makes its own crust.
This can be used as egg pie.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add the dry ingredients.
Shape into ball size of a small walnut.
Dip in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: schnitzel franconian(yields 5 to 6 servings)
directions: Brown veal patties in hot oil in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Simmer only long enough for vegetables to be hot.
Do not overcook.
Tomatoes and onions should be on the crunchy side.
Serve over hot rice.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, onion, water chestnuts, cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise in a casserole.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Dribble margarine on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: party potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions, bouillon cubes and celery in 3 quarts of water. When potatoes are done, fry bacon
crispy and in small pieces. Put bacon in potatoes, celery, onion mixture. Add Velveeta cheese and sour cream. Cook until all melted. Serve with hot bread.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Cook raisins in water for 5 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger and vinegar.
Add to water and raisins and cook until slightly thickened.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well with vanilla.
Add flour gradually until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Chill the dough.
Mold about 1 tablespoon cookie dough around each chocolate kiss, covering kiss completely.

title: mint cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in bowl in microwave for 1 minute.
Stir, then continue cooking for 25 seconds until chocolate is melted.
Drop Ritz crackers into chocolate; turn over with fork and place on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, eggs and water; beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats, butterscotch morsels and orange extract.
Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Cook flour, butter and milk (do not boil).
Add cheese and melt.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle dry mustard and mix.

title: cathedral cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, semi-sweet chocolate chips and margarine over low heat.
When melted, add beaten eggs and cook on very low heat for one minute.
Cool completely.
Put marshmallows and pecans in a large bowl.
Pour well cooked mixture over marshmallows and pecans until well coated.
On waxed paper with sifted powdered sugar on it, spoon out to form roll.
Refrigerate and cut into desired slices.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 375°.
Remove 1 pie crust shell from freezer.
Meanwhile, combine filling ingredients in order given.
Recrimp edge of pie shell to stand 1/2-inch above rim.
Place pie shell on preheated cookie sheet, near center of oven.
Working quickly, pour filling into pie shell.
Bake for 70 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Garnish with whipped cream and walnuts, if desired.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: marinated baked ham
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Pour over ham slice; cover and chill 8 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally. Drain ham, reserving marinade.
Place ham in a shallow baking pan; bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes, basting every 10 minutes with reserved marinade.

title: wolfe's cornbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and shortening; beat until smooth.
Bake in 8-inch square greased pan for 20 to 25 minutes in 425° oven.
Serve hot with butter and honey.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Whisk together vinegar, oil, water, pickle juice, salt and pepper.
Lightly toss all ingredients, except tomatoes, with dressing.
Refrigerate.
Add tomatoes as garnish when serving.

title: sweet and sour weenies
directions: Mix together. Heat and serve. Better if cooked a little while together.

title: greek meatballs
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Place in a mixing bowl.
Cover with a small amount of water.
Gently squeeze bread to drain excess water.
Return bread to a bowl.
Add meat, egg, onion and whatever herb you have chosen.
Salt and pepper.
Mix well with hands. Shape into 2-inch patties; coat well with flour.
Fry patties over high heat in mixture of butter and oil.
Turn once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with pilaf and a hot vegetable, or add to spaghetti sauce.
Serves 4.

title: hopscotch candy
directions: Place the peanut butter and butterscotch morsels in double boiler over hot water, not boiling.
Melt together.
Stir until blended.
Add the chow mein noodles and the marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Chill 30 minutes.
Makes about 30.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan or in a crock-pot.
Sprinkle the reserved cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 or 2 hours on high in a crock-pot.

title: critter crunch
directions: Combine sugar and margarine in a small bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until margarine melts.
Add cinnamon. Combine remaining ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle with margarine mixture, tossing gently to coat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool completely. Store in airtight container.
Makes 7 cups.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water and pinch of sugar. Mix together the 1/2 cup sugar, salt, shortening and mashed potatoes.
Add scalded milk, flour and yeast.
Add eggs.
Dough should be stiff enough to knead well (mix with a wooden spoon), then turn out on board and knead until elastic.
Put in warm place to rise.
When double in bulk (takes 1 1/2 hours), divide in 2 parts.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Fold over.
Place on baking sheets and let rise until very light.
Bake at about 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 60 rolls.

title: baked vegetables
directions: Cut all vegetables to desired sizes.
Mix together well.
Put all vegetables in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
(Spray dish with Pam before adding vegetables.)
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove.
Stir well or turn vegetables.
Continue cooking until tender.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Pat into a loaf pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven until done.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add oil and buttermilk alternately with 3 cups flour and remaining dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Mix remaining 1 cup flour with the last 4 ingredients, then add to first mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: *You may substitute scallops for the shrimp.

title: raisin bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine butter, sugar, salt and milk (cooled).
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; beat well.
Add yeast and eggs; beat well.
Add raisins.
Stir in enough flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface and knead until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let double in warm place (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Make a "well" in the center.
Mix the liquid ingredients together and pour into the "well."
Blend together with a spoon until the dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened.
Evenly distribute into 12-cup muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the middle of a muffin comes out clean. Let cool for about 30 minutes for best texture.

title: cinnamon nut swirls
directions: To the hot roll mix add the yeast and sugar.
Mix according to directions on package.
Raise double.
Roll out into 9 x 13-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add it to sugar.
Roll; cut into 3/4-inch slices.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil in large boiler.
Stir in gelatin mix.
Let cool.
Add whipped topping, stirring well.
Add the buttermilk and mix well.
Congeal.
Mixture is delicious.

title: 10 minute mousse pie
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave or double boiler.
Meanwhile, prepare mousse according to package directions, adding Espresso powder before beating.
Scrape chocolate into a medium-size bowl. Stir in about 1/3 mousse mixture and nuts.
Spread over bottom of pie crust.
Spread remaining mousse on top, mounding slightly in center.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip over top in swirls.
Garnish with chocolate shavings or cookies or sprinkle extra chips and nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring broccoli to a boil with 2 cups water.
Boil broccoli two minutes.
Drain broccoli.
Mix all other ingredients together with 1/2 stick of crackers.
Melt butter in casserole dish; add 1/2 butter to mixture.	Add 1/2 of crushed Ritz to bottom and add other 1/2 crumbs to the top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until crackers are golden brown.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In a large saucepan, cook noodles.
Drain and toss with olive oil.
Place noodles in two 7 x 11-inch greased baking dishes, spreading noodles up sides of dishes.
In a medium bowl, combine chicken, soup, sour cream, water chestnuts, sherry, tarragon and peppers.
Pour soup mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and poppy seed over soup mixture.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: stuffed ground beef rolls
directions: In
a bowl, blend ground beef, egg, salt, pepper, bread crumbs and
water; mixture will feel quite moist.
Cut a strip of waxed paper
inches
long,
moisten top side.
Form a 4 inch wide strip
of
the
meat mixture the length of the waxed paper.
Cut cream cheese into 8 sticks.
Place them along the length of the ground
beef,
end
to
end.
Roll up.
Pick up waxed paper to help to lift the meat over the filling; you'll form a
lengthwise roll.
Cut
into 8 pieces crosswise.
Dust each piece with flour on all sides.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in frying pan.
Brown rolls on all sides, cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove
onto warm
plate.
Stir
flour
into pan drippings.
Slowly
add
the broth,
whisking
to
keep sauce smooth.
Cook
until thickened. Stir in sour cream and tarragon.
Pour sauce over rolls.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl or bowl of electric mixer, sprinkle yeast over the water.
Add 1 tablespoon of the sugar.
Let stand about 5 minutes, until yeast is soft.
Add remaining sugar, milk, salt and softened butter.
Mix in 2 1/2 cups of the flour; beat until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Beat in eggs, one a a time. Stir in about 2 more cups of flour to make a soft dough.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets in bite size pieces.
Trim stalk of tough outer skin and chop, also.
Mix vegetables together; toss well with dressing.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crush crackers and blend in 1 tablespoon sugar and butter.
Put in bottom of a large oblong baking dish (9 x 13-inches).
Cream cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla together; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well and spread over cracker mixture. Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Cool 5 minutes.
Mix sour cream, 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar.
Put on top of baked cake and bake 10 minutes.
Cool and keep in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oil, vanilla, beat until thick.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins or currants, walnuts, zucchini and crushed pineapple.
Blend together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together first three ingredients, then add onion, salt and pepper.
Roll into small balls and brown in skillet with enough oil to cover bottom of skillet. Continuously flip or roll balls so not to burn.
Does not take long to brown balls. After browning, add to sauce and let simmer with sauce.

title: chocolate covered toffee
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook and stir until it reaches 300°.
Quickly stir in 1 cup of nuts.
Take off stove and pour onto cookie sheet.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate and spread on toffee.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts. Cool and break into pieces.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix onion, green peppers and cabbage.
Place in casserole dish in layers.
Pour tomato soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and butter in 2-cup microwavable bowl.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 minutes; stir. Microwave 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes more or until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda and pour over cereal mixture; stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on baking sheet; break into pieces.
Makes 10 cups.

title: apple spice muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Blend or sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir in chopped, peeled apple. Make a well in center of dry ingredients. Combine and add egg, milk and vegetable oil or melted shortening. Stir only until combined. (The batter should be lumpy.) Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. This makes 10 medium-sized muffins. They can be baked in paper baking muffin cups in ungreased muffin pan too.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured heavy cookie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: egg strata
directions: Cube bread and layer in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish; add ham or sausage and cheese in layers. Mix milk, eggs and dry mustard together. Pour over bread and meat. Pour butter over all. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball candy cane
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in pineapple, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt.
Refrigerate until firm.
Form into the shape of a candy cane.
Use pimento slices for red striping.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 20.

title: french texas toast
directions: Gently crack eggs into pan or large bowl.
Add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Whisk until blended.
Dip the bread into egg mixture to coat each side.
Place in heated frypan and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side until golden brown.

title: sam's circle
directions: In a saucepan, mix water, 1/2 cup butter, 1 teaspoon sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour and beat with a wooden spoon until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat and beat in 4 eggs one at a time (this is important).

title: butternut squash souffle
directions: Squash will need to be cut up and cooked.
Cook squash until it is soft.
Combine all ingredients and put in a baking dish. Add topping.

title: sauce for 200 lbs meat
directions: Put all in a pot, cook at 200 degrees. Stir often. Cook about 1 1/2 hours. If you don't use it all put in
jars and seal like fruit. Will keep for 1 year.

title: pat's cottage cheese rounds
directions: Combine flour, butter, cottage cheese and salt.
Shape into ball.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch rounds or roll into log shape about 2 inches in diameter.
Chill and later slice 1/2 inch thick.
Brush tops of rounds with beaten egg yolk.
Bake on greased sheet at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: strawberry margaritas
directions: Chill 2 glasses. Rub rims with water and coat rim with sugar. Blend ice cream, cut up strawberries, tequila and lime juice in blender until smooth and fill glasses.
Add club soda. Garnish with whole strawberries and lime slices.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and let set in refrigerator.
Set aside other half until later.

title: goat cheese tartletts with sun dried tomatoes
directions: Roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with round cutter and place in muffin tin presprayed with nonstick spray.
Prick dough with fork and bake about 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
(Not completely done.)

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and undissolved jello, then add other ingredients.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato balls(thanksgiving dinner - mallory farms)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes.
Peel and thoroughly cream them with butter.
Add orange juice and sherry to taste.
Form a ball of sweet potatoes around a marshmallow.
Roll balls in corn flakes and deep fry until golden brown.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Mix jello with water.
Mix together ingredients.
Crush wafers and line pan.
Pour in mixture. Top with crumbs.
Chill.

title: oatmeal crackers
directions: Mix ingredients and roll out onto 2 large cookie sheets.
Roll thin.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mark in squares or diamonds.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until crisp.
Watch edges so they don't burn.

title: no fat chicken
directions: Remove skin and all fat from chicken. Rinse. Pat dry chicken. Sprinkle seasonings to taste.
Spray frying pan with no stick cooking spray.
Place on medium heat.
Place chicken, meaty side down.
Simmer covered for 15 minutes.
Turn.
Repeat. Simmer. Remove cover and let juices cook out.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease dish holding 6 cups.
Mix in bowl
flour,
dry
milk, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Blend in	margarine
until
a crumbly mixture is formed.	Put apples
in dish and then sprinkle sugar-cinnamon mixture over apples; sprinkle
crumb
topping over apples.
Bake on center of oven 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm.

title: orange-almond salad
directions: In screw-top jar, combine oil, sugar, salt and almond extract. Cover and shake well to dissolve sugar and salt.
Chill.
At serving time, in large salad bowl, combine salad greens, oranges, celery and onion.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Pour dressing over and toss gently to coat.
Serve at once.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: shake and bake mix for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and store at room temperature.
To use this version of coating mix, dip fryer pieces first into milk and then into bag filled with 2 cups of coating mixture.
Shake.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly oiled cookie tin and bake uncovered at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
One cup coats 2 pounds of chicken fryer pieces.
Yield:
7 cups of mix.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut vegetables into flowerets.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together and pour over vegetables and cheese.
Mix well and add crumbled bacon.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Slice bananas into food processor.
Add margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
Add raisins and beat.
Pour into loaf pan and bake in oven at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; wait 10 minutes before cutting.
Cream cheese spread on top is very good.
The average banana has only 100 calories and is very high in potassium content.

title: egg rolls
directions: Note: Carrot and/or green pepper can also be used.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the ingredients well and top with cubed Velveeta cheese. Bake or microwave for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Then add crushed potato chips to top and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients together for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered wax paper.

title: kentucky chicken
directions: Mix together bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Dip each breast in butter, then roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange pieces of chicken in a shallow roasting pan. Pour remaining butter on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruited cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; grate Monterey cheese.
Chop remaining ingredients very fine and combine with cheeses.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans to cover.
Serve with Nabisco gingersnaps.

title: mom's sauerkraut and dumplings
directions: Place enough pork cut into nice pieces into covered roaster and put into medium oven for about 1 1/2 hours with enough kraut according to amount of pork.
To make dumplings, mix flour, egg, baking powder, salt and enough milk to form a soft dough.
Put spoonfuls over kraut.
Return to oven for 1/2 hour.
"Don't remove lid for 1/2 hour or the dumplings will get soggy."

title: cajun shrimp and rice
directions: Cook all ingredients in a large saucepan for about 20 to 30 minutes over medium heat.
Prepare approximately 12 ounces of rice according to package directions.
(Cooking time is usually to minute.)
When rice is cooked and drained, add about 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Spoon rice onto plates and top with shrimp sauce. Served with a sprig of parsley, this dish makes an attractive main course for any meal.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cocoons
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and vanilla.
Roll in finger-size cocoons.
Bake at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Fry bacon (save drippings).
Lay bacon on paper towels and drain while sauteing onion and green pepper in bacon drippings.
Crumble bacon into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pinwheel crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open dough, unroll and leave in two long rectangular pieces.
Spread cream cheese on top of each piece of dough.
Roll up dough and slice into 1/2-inch pinwheels.
Lay flat on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.

title: creamy brussel casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, add all ingredients except sprouts.
Cook until bubbly in a 350° oven or 5 minutes in a microwave.
Add the Brussels sprouts and cook again (for bake 10 minutes or microwave another 2 minutes).

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll ground beef into patties and roll in flour.
Put patties in casserole and pour 1 to 2 cans of mushroom soup over patties. Cover and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: venison bologna
directions: Mix well.
Make 5 rolls and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Put rolls in refrigerator for 3 days.
Take out once each day and roll while still in Saran Wrap to make firm.
After 3rd day, unwrap and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: m&m's party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make white sauce with first 4 ingredients.
Melt cheese into white sauce. Combine crushed wafers and 1 stick of butter.
Line a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with wafer mixture (save some for topping).
Combine asparagus, toasted almonds and cheese/white sauce and pour into casserole dish.
Top with remaining wafer mixture. Bake at 450° about 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pack firmly in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pecan fingers
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 4 strips.	Mix coconut and pecans.
Dip bread strips
into
milk,
then roll into coconut mixture.
Place on greased cookie
sheet
and
bake
to 12 minutes at 350°, or until golden brown.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Be creative.
Add in your favorites (i.e. green pepper, oregano, bacon bits, sausage, etc.).

title: meat balls and sauce
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and form into balls.
Brown in hot fat.
Saute chopped onion, celery and bell pepper together with garlic salt.
Add small can of tomato sauce and sugar.
Cook until deep red.
Add small can of tomatoes and cook over low heat for 2 hours or longer.
Add water if sauce becomes too thick.
Add meat balls and cook 30 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Blend cake mix, egg and oleo; press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with pie filling.
Over pie filling sprinkle brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Mix sour cream and egg in small bowl.
When mixed well, spread over top of mixture in baking dish. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Very easy, quick and good!

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 can of tomato sauce. Use 1 can sauce to top peppers before baking. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chef's salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl.
Arrange chicken, ham, eggs and cheese on top of salad.
Arrange cucumber slices around edge of bowl.
Serve with your favorite dressing.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush Oreos and combine with melted margarine. Spread crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch dish.

Let ice cream become soft enough to spread onto crumbs. Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Return to freezer until firm. Spread with whipped topping. Drizzle with more chocolate syrup and sprinkle with toasted pecans. Cover and return to freezer.

title: cheese cubes
directions: Mix over low heat in a heavy pan the margarine, cheese and cream cheese.
When cheeses are melted and all mixed together, turn heat off.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Cube French bread into 1-inch cubes.
Line a cookie sheet with foil.
With tongs, dip bread cubes in cheese mixture. Place single layer on foil.
Freeze them in a plastic bag and keep frozen.
Bake on foiled lined pan at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes. Serve.

title: potato and beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and then boil potatoes after cutting them in slices.
Layer them in a casserole dish; top with half of ground beef, then a layer of cheese.
Layer again and then mix up soup with water as on can.
Pour over casserole.
Bake until all is bubbling all the way through.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Mix well. Serve over penne pasta or with grilled chicken or crab meat is excellent.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil water and add macaroni.
When tender, remove from stove and drain.
Put in cake pan and add cheese and butter.
Pour in milk slowly.
Let it float through macaroni.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese candies
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and extract.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar.
Knead in remaining confectioners sugar until smooth.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in colored sugar if desired.
Place on ungreased baking sheets; flatten with a fork.
Let stand for 1 hour to harden.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine rotini and 1/4 cup salad dressing; toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Combine red pepper strips and remaining ingredients; add rotini and toss gently.
Serve chilled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, then drain the liquid.
In a mixing bowl, combine soup, Miracle Whip, cheese and eggs.
Mix well and fold into broccoli.
Pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over casserole; top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add sugar, milk and salt.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Drop 2 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla, then cool.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into a greased pan.
Add 1 cup nuts, if desired.

title: russian dressing
directions: A touch of honey makes this special.

title: pecan pie number 3
directions: Beat eggs slightly in medium size bowl.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt, corn syrup and vanilla.
Pour into prepared shell.
Arrange pecan halves in pattern on top or chop pecans coarsely and sprinkle into shell before adding filling.
Bake in preheated moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes or until center is almost set. (Do not overbake, for filling will set as it cools.)
Cool on a wire rack.

title: sweetheart punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in 2 quarts cold water.
Add pineapple juice to jello.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.
Makes approximately 35 servings.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed on package.
Brown ground beef in a large iron skillet or electric skillet.
Add all remaining ingredients except the cheese and spaghetti. Stir well; add well drained spaghetti.
Place lid on skillet and simmer about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove lid; add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix and let set overnight.
Next day, add 1 can mandarin oranges (drained).

title: red christmas cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Mix food coloring and cocoa together; add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour and salt alternately with buttermilk and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Combine vinegar and soda; add to mixture while still foaming.

title: sparkling cranberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In small bowl combine cranberries and 2 tbsp. sugar.
In large bowl stir together flour, 1/3 c.
sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Stir in juice and egg until just moist.
Gently stir in cranberry mixture.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake for 20-25 minutes, until golden.
Cool 5 minutes, remove from tins.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, salad oil and pudding.
After mixing well, add 7-Up and pour into a well-greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Stir in fruits and nuts.
Chill batter.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl. Beat egg in small bowl and add other liquids. Add liquids to dry ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350 approximately 15 minutes.

title: beef in casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, salt, sugar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic and pepper in a skillet.
Cook until meat loses red color. Set aside.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: marble bars
directions: Stir together corn syrup, sugar and margarine in large saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil over heat for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs until frothy; beat in oil and sugar.
Add chocolate and flavoring.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Squeeze excess moisture from zucchini in colander. Add to mixture, then nuts and dates.
Pour in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes or until done.
Let stand inverted on rack 20 minutes and glaze with chocolate icing.
I only use 1/2 the icing.

title: butterscotch pinwheels
directions: Melt chocolate and 2 tablespoons shortening in microwave. Remove from heat.
Add milk, flour, and vanilla.
Blend well. Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan which has been greased and lined with waxed paper and greased again.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes. Immediately turn chocolate out onto a towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Spread with filling.
Sprinkle with nuts. Roll up, starting at 15 inch side.
Wrap and chill for 6 hours. Cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind nuts, eggs and olives together. Add mayonnaise and mix well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together with hands and roll into marble-sized balls. Bake at 370° about 10 minutes.
These freeze nicely.

title: italian delight(prepare the day before.)
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package until tender. Drain.

title: sherried apricot soup
directions: Drain apricot halves and place in a food processor. Add the remaining ingredients and pulse on and off until blended. Chill until ready to use. Garnish with fresh mint leaves.

title: shrimp spread or dip
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Stir into soup.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased mold.
Allow to set before removing.

title: south texas red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak 8 hours.
Drain.
Add ham bone, salt pork and 2 quarts water.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove and discard ham bone and salt pork.
Add tomatoes and next 8 ingredients; stir well.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage and simmer, uncovered, an additional hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove and discard bay leaves. Serve over rice.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Combine the gelatin and water; bring to a boil.
Gently beat cream cheese and soup until blended.
Add gelatin to soup mixture and blend well.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Place in a gelatin mold and chill for 2 hours.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place apples in a baking dish. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar on top of apples.
Pour 1/3 box of cake mix on top of apples and cinnamon sugar.
Pour melted butter or margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until apples are cooked.

title: hummus
directions: Use metal blade in food processor.
Drop garlic into processor while running.
Chop until fine.
Add all other ingredients and blend until smooth.
Add reserved liquid, as needed, if too thick. Serve with wedges of pita bread.

title: ham raisin sauce
directions: Boil raisins five minutes in water.
Add 1/3 sugar mixed with cornstarch, spices, salt and mustard.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Blend in vinegar.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce on hot ham.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients until it threads.
Add the peanuts. Cook until dark brown. Remove from heat and add the soda. Stir good and put on buttered cookie sheet.
Spread thin. Cool.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, baking powder and soda and add to mixture alternately with sour cream. Stir in flavoring. Pour into greased and floured pans. Will take 3 loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes and then start checking to see if it is done. If you use a bundt pan, bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: To make marinade and sauce:
Heat oil in medium saucepan; add onions and sugar. Saute until onions are golden (6 minutes). Mix in wine and next 5 ingredients. Cook 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat; cool completely.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Mix together sugar, Crisco, eggs, soda, salt, milk, orange juice and 2 cups flour.
Dredge fruit and nuts in remaining 1 cup flour until well coated.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° until light brown.
Store in airtight container or cookie tin.

title: acomb molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll dough into one-inch balls.
Roll balls in small amount of granulated sugar lightly to coat.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet approximately 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These are soft cookies, reminding one of a gingersnap.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Sprinkle rice evenly over bottom of buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Mix milk and sugar.
Pour over rice; sprinkle with nutmeg and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes for first 1 1/2 hours. Serve warm if you like, topped with cream.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Drain.
Then mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend butter, 2 cups flour and powdered sugar and press in a greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Beat sugar, 1/2 cup flour, lemon juice, eggs and baking powder together and pour over crust.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: 3 layer dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, taco seasoning and mayonnaise.
Layer refried beans then sour cream mixture.
Top with chopped tomato, green onions, Cheddar cheese and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp log
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp.
Mix all ingredients in blender or food processor until smooth.
Shape into two loaves.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: miniature party reubens
directions: Stack corned beef, sauerkraut and swiss cheese on cocktail rye bread.
Broil in oven until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger meat, then drain it.
Stir in chicken soup, then mushroom soup, stirring well to mix.
Add the enchilada sauce.
Heat mixture, stirring to mix and heat through.
Layer Dorito chips in the bottom of casserole dish.
Pour the meat mixture over chips; put cheese on top.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until bubbly around the sides in a 350° oven.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter/margarine with sugars.
Add egg, water and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt, cloves, cinnamon and baking soda; stir in.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins!
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: chicken and corn
directions: Cook chicken/hen until tender.
Debone and salt to taste.
Add corn to 1 pint of boiling broth.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
More broth may be added if needed to thin mixture.
The corn will determine the amount of broth needed. Young and tender corn requires less broth.
Add deboned chicken to corn and cook an additional 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: stove top creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, sugar, salt and milk in a saucepan.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Combine egg yolk, cornstarch and water.
Stir into the rice mixture along with the raisins about 15 minutes before cooking time is finished.
Pour into serving dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: beef and cheese crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef, onions and peppers.
Drain. Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms and garlic salt.
Let simmer. Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in 9-inch ungreased casserole dish.
Press edges together over sides and bottom. Combine egg and 1 cup cheese.
Spread over crust.
Spoon hot mixture over this.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marinated sliced tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes; arrange in a shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over tomatoes.
Chill, covered, for 1 hour.

title: lazy day beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake, uncovered, at 250° for 3 hours.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop into patties into a hot skillet to fry.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; simmer about 5 minutes. Makes 1 1/2 cups of sauce.

title: ribbon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add the beaten egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add the dry ingredients:
flour, baking powder and salt; blend together.
Divide the dough into 3 parts.
To the first add 1/4 cup candied cherries, cut up, and the red food coloring.
To the second part, add the chopped nuts and melted chocolate.
To third part, add the poppy seed.
Blend each part thoroughly.
Line an ice cube tray or long narrow bread pan with waxed paper.
Layer dough into pan in order made.
Chill overnight.
Next day, preheat oven to 400°.
Turn dough onto a cutting board and slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Bake on greased cookie sheets for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients well.
Put a vanilla wafer in a cupcake cup.
Fill and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add topping.

title: aunt sam's memory cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add.
Add pecans.
Shape into 2 (16-inch) rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; add sugar and cocoa. Pour in milk. Bring to a boil; boil 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until well mixed. Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: shrimp puffs
directions: Toast bread lightly.
(If using white bread, trim crust and cut into 4 squares.)
Mix other ingredients.
Top bread with mixture.
Broil 1 minute.
Serve hot.

title: e-z soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain grease.
Add ingredients; bring to boil, then simmer 1 hour.

title: rice and beef "porcupines"
directions: Mix beef, rice, onions and seasonings.
Form into small balls.
Fry in hot oil, turning frequently, until brown (light), but not on all sides.
Add tomato sauce and water; mix well. Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no-fail pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in Crisco, 1 cup at a time.
Beat egg yolk and milk.
Add to flour mixture and mix.
Divide into 8 portions.
Freeze leftover dough.
Makes 4 double pies.
Bake filled pies at 425° for 45 minutes.
Dough will be soft.
Roll out on floured dish towel.
Flip over rolling pin and place into pie plate.
Trim sides.

title: cold rice and green peas
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
When cooked, add all of the ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate a few hours and serve cold.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water; set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening, salt and eggs; mix long.
Add cold water and yeast mixture.
Add flour (mixture is not stiff).
Cover with towel and let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Punch down and divide dough in half.
Cut in strips (big dumplings).

title: chicken macaroni salad
directions: Cook chicken and cool; cut in small pieces.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Chop all vegetables and shred the carrots.
Mix all together.
Season to taste.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and molasses.
Stir in water.
Mix dry ingredients and add.
Chill dough.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Place far apart on lightly greased sheets.
Bake at 350° until no imprint when touched, about 15 minutes.
When cool, spread with glaze of confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla.
(These will stay lovely and soft if you watch them carefully and remove from oven before the bottoms brown.)

title: chicken in lemon sauce(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix carrots, celery, onions and parsley together.
Add to mixture the wine, lemon juice, lemon peel, basil leaves, thyme leaves, lemon pepper, salt and chicken bouillon.
Combine all together in a 1-quart casserole to make sauce for chicken.
Cover; microwave at High 1 to 4 minutes, or until vegetables are starting to get tender.
Make sure about halfway through, you stir the mixture.
Skin and cut up the chicken fryer.
Arrange in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with meatiest portions on the outside.
Pour sauce over the chicken.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 15 minutes; rearrange and baste with sauce every 5 minutes. Reduce power to 50% or Medium; microwave 4 to 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, basting 2 or 3 times.
Skim fat from cooking liquid.

title: apricot delight
directions: Cook oleo, eggs and sugar until thick.
Roll and crush vanilla wafers fine.
Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with 2/3 of the crumbs.
Put cooked ingredients on top of crumbs.
When cool, add 1/2 cup nuts, 1/2 of the Cool Whip, then layer with apricots, then remainder of cream, nuts and crumbs.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop teaspoonsful of dough into powdered sugar. Roll in sugar.
Shape into balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: french canadian pork pie(a koljonen christmas breakfast tradition)
directions: Mix together flour and shortening to the consistency of fine corn meal.
Add water.
Knead well to make a smooth and firm dough.
Cover and set aside.
Refrigerate if dough is not used within a couple hours.

title: kolaches
directions: Soak yeast in warm water with sugar.
Mix milk, margarine, sugar and salt in a microwave bowl and warm until sugar is dissolved and margarine is melted.
Cool to lukewarm and add vanilla.
Meanwhile, beat egg in mixing bowl, add yeast mixture and milk mixture.
Add enough flour for a soft dough.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Pour out on well floured board or counter.
Knead lightly.
Pinch off small amount and make into rolls, place on well greased baking pan about 1/2-inch apart.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down center of rolls and add fruit pie filling.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Glaze while hot.

title: fudge
directions: Heat sugar, milk, cocoa, corn syrup and salt.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Cool.
Add butter and vanilla. Beat until thick and begins to lose its gloss, about 3 minutes. Pour into greased pan and let cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a 10-inch skillet.
Cook until peanuts crack and get thick and dark in color.
Add baking soda, stir well and pour into buttered cookie sheet (12 x 18-inch).
Have soda ready, pan buttered, to pour and spread candy.

title: lou's easy chops
directions: Brown chops in small amount of oil (or use nonstick pan and no oil) to seal both sides (do not cook through).
Pat oil off chops. Mix above ingredients together.
Arrange chops in baking dish; pour mixture over chops.
Bake in a 350° oven for 3/4 hour, or until tender.
Do not overcook.
If mixture is too dry, add more wine to make more liquid.
If left as is, it may caramelize while baking.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 2 layers at 350°.
Slice layers when cooled completely.

title: cathedral window cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour and salt and beat until smooth.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate and margarine in a 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly until smooth.
Stir in sugar and eggs and beat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread over cookie base.
Chill 2 hours. Cut in bars.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Wash cabbage; cut out core.
Cook whole in boiling water until barely tender; drain.
Combine next 8 ingredients.
Separate about 8 large leaves.
Put spoonful of mixture in each leaf; roll up, tucking in ends.
In hot fat in Dutch oven, saute onion with next 3 ingredients about 10 minutes.
Add hot water.
Place rolls on top of onion.
Mix tomato sauce with 1/4 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini pickles - sweet
directions: Boil together for 10 minutes.
You can add green food coloring (1 tablespoon).
Let stand overnight and then bring to a boil and boil all together for 30 to 35 minutes or until zucchini is clear looking.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and syrup.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour in shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 40 to 50 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cut steak into small pieces; salt and pepper and dredge in flour. Brown to golden color in skillet.
Pour off excess oil. Cover with onion rings and potatoes; salt and pepper as desired. Add water to soup and mix.
Pour over meat, potatoes and onion rings. Cover and cook over low heat until tender.

title: pea salad
directions: Empty mayo into large bowl.
Pour in a small amount of pickle juice and mix until mayo is the thick side of runny.
Add pepper and salt for taste.
Add peas, cheese and mushrooms.
Stir to mix. Refrigerate and serve in decorative bowl.
Great for potlucks.

title: seven layer lettuce salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Tupperware dish, layer lettuce, onion, peas (peas should be rinsed and drained), crumbled bacon and sliced eggs.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar.
Spread on top of layers. Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top of Miracle Whip mixture. Refrigerate.

title: orange cream cheese muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg and juice; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients only until moistened. Fold in pecans.
Grease 6 jumbo muffin pans generously.
Fill cups 1/2 full.
Spoon 1 teaspoon marmalade into the center of each muffin.
Divide the remaining batter over the marmalade.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in preheated oven.

title: flounder with oil
directions: Boil flounder approximately 8 to 10 minutes or until cooked. Remove from water; place on platter.
Cook oil until almost boiled; pour over flounder immediately (should sizzle).
Add shoyu and green onions.
Serve immediately.

title: cocktail pizzas
directions: Brown sausage.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until cheese is melted.
Spread on party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: belgian cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Form into ball; sprinkle with chopped parsley (dried).
Serve with small crackers.

title: arancini alla zia lina
directions: Boil rice in salted water and drain.
Let set several hours or overnight.
Rice must be very dry.
Place rice in bowl.
Add 1 egg, Romano cheese and parsley.
Shape into flat cakes with indentation in center.
Fill with peas and sausage mixture, heated in sauce. Place 2 to 3 chunks Provolone on.
Roll rice into balls, making sure no stuffing seeps out.
Roll in beaten eggs and then bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil; drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Combine water and undrained tomatoes, bouillon, basil and oregano.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in frozen vegetables and tortellini.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 7 minutes or until tortellini are tender.
Add parsley.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325°.

title: munchible macaroons
directions: Blend Dairy Sweet sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in coconut and cereal.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 250° oven 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 48.

title: ham and lentil soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, bring ham bone and water to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Remove ham bone. To broth, add lentils, tomatoes, carrots, celery, onions and seasonings; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until lentils and vegetables are tender. Meanwhile, remove ham from bone; coarsely chop. Add ham, sausage and parsley to soup; heat through. Yield: 10 to 12 servings (3 quarts).

title: cucumber-tomato salad
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise in quarters, then in 3/4-inch chunks. Cut tomatoes in like-size pieces and feather-slice onion.
Add salt and Italian dressing.
Toss and place in bowl lined with lettuce leaves.

title: cheesy crescent twist-ups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine first 3 ingredients.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 long strips. Spread about 1/4 of cheese mixture over one strip.
Place a second strip on top of first; spread with another 1/4 of cheese mixture. Place a third dough strip on top.
Cut filled strip crosswise into 8 pieces.
Repeat process with second large rectangle.
Twist each strip; seal ends.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 16 snacks.

title: corned beef dip
