directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Finely chop corned beef (thin sliced luncheon meat).
Chop green onions.
Mix all together adding Worcestershire to taste and mayonnaise for spreading consistency. Serve with Triscuits or other type crackers.

title: old fashioned christmas chocolate
directions: Mix & cook sugar, butter, milk, and cocoa for 20 min., stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla, peanuts (crushed), and flour.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Tear lettuce and spinach.
Slice hard-boiled eggs and green onions.
Mix all.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients except cabbage (set aside).
Fill a large kettle with water and place cored cabbage in it.
Boil until leaves start to come apart from heat.
Remove leaves and drain. Fill each leaf with meat mixture.
Roll and serve with toothpick. Bake 3 hours at 350°.
As they bake, pour tomato sauce over. While baking, top with bacon.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cut shrimp up and mix all together.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: In skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook rice and onions with basil until rice is slightly brown; stir constantly.
Stir in broth.
Heat to boiling.
Add chicken. Reduce heat to medium.
Cover; cook 5 minutes.
Add vegetables. Cover; cook 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and rice is tender, stirring rice mixture occasionally.
Garnish chicken with lemon slice and sprinkle with paprika.

title: angel wings(italian kruspla)
directions: Add salt to eggs and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar and eggs and continue to beat.
Add sour cream and flour alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Knead on floured board until the dough blisters.
Cut dough into strips and roll very thin.
Cut strips about 4-inches long.
Slit each piece in center and pull one end through the slit.
Fry in deep oil until lightly browned.
Drain on toweling and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients, pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over the top with oleo. Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fettucine with blue cheese(gorgonzola)
directions: Let the Gorgonzola and margarine remain at room temperature until soft.
When soft, mix Gorgonzola, margarine and other cheese.
Cook fettucine or any other pasta.
Drain pasta and place in a frying pan.
Add other ingredients and mix in with pasta. Cook for about two minutes.
Serve.
Add additional grated cheese, if desired.

title: very easy peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter, sugar and milk.
In separate bowl, beat whipping cream until stiff.
(Do not underbeat.)
Fold together the whipped cream with the peanut butter mixture until smooth.
Spread into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: onion and chive dip
directions: Chop onion; lightly saute in butter.
Mix on high speed the cream cheese and milk.
Add all ingredients to cream cheese mixture and stir well with a fork.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients. Beat for about 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yummy warm.

title: tuna salad biscayne
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Combine with remaining ingredients except parsley or watercress.
Mix lightly and chill.
Garnish with parsley or watercress.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pa's 5 minute fudge
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Pour in mixture of flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Add to defined fruit.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Slowly add the milk, continuing to beat the mixture until well blended.
Add vanilla and lemon juice; blend well.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Top with cherry pie filling and serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: beets
directions: Mix all ingredients together, let stand for 1 hour.
This may be served hot or cold.
Serves 4.

title: easy cream cheese mints
directions: Knead like pie dough to smooth texture.
Form into balls; flatten with fork.
Refrigerate.

title: king ranch
directions: Grease large casserole dish.
Dip tart shells in broth and line dish with shells.
Layer ingredients as follows:
chicken, onion, pepper, soups and tomatoes and juice (mashed with fork).
Cover completely with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: leftover pie
directions: Mix dough by stirring together flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in lard until the mixture has a fine grainy appearance.
Try not to handle the dough too much.
Add milk and blend all together.
Roll out the dough in a circle if you want to make a crescent or a rectangle if you want to roll it up.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus in buttered dish (9-inch square). Cover with a cream of mushroom soup. Mix into asparagus lightly.
Add a little water to clean out can.
Cover with a sprinkling of Worcestershire sauce.
Top with crackers and egg slices.
Melt margarine and drizzle over top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chili and beans
directions: You can use small pieces of salt pork in beans, but I take it out before I add the other ingredients.
I cook pinto beans in crock-pot.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Stir margarine into hot spaghetti.
Add Parmesan and well-beaten eggs.
Use 9 x 13-inch buttered (Pam) and form crust with the spaghetti.
Spread spaghetti sauce on crust. Add hamburger or Italian sausage uncooked, then Mozzarella cheese, then olives and onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Then add pepperoni and bake for additional 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Ad almonds and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: auflaufa
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Grease a large
pan.
Bake at 350°.
Will bubble and get golden brown when done, approximately 25 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: meat stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to package.
Stuff with meat filling:
Mix meat, egg, 1/2 the Mozzarella, bread and milk. Season with salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix well.

title: cream cheese
directions: Heat milk to 115° and cook 1/2 hour.
Strain through cloth and squeeze out whey. Add soda and butter; let stand 2 hours.
Add 1 cup cream and set in pan of boiling water.
Beat lumps out. When smooth, add 1/2 cup cream and salt.
Put into buttered glass dish. Let set 5 days.
If not used in another 5 days, cover with melted paraffin.

title: jogging in a jug drink(good for your health)
directions: Mix all together.
Drink a glass every morning.
Pour over ice to drink.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onion and beef together.
Add all 3 cans of soup and one cup water.
Cook in slow cooker
until meat is tender.
(I cook it all day on low heat.)
Cook noodles.
Place stroganoff over noodles and serve.
"Fast and very good."

title: sausage and smothered potatoes
directions: In large pan, put 2 to 3 tablespoons of oil.
Brown sliced sausage.
Add onion and cook 2 to 3 minutes with sausage.
Add potatoes and season with salt and pepper.
Mix together and cook covered over low fire until potatoes are tender.
Stir often because potatoes will stick to pan.

title: janis' halloween haystacks
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk in a bowl.
Mix in powdered sugar gradually.
Stir in the melted chocolate, vanilla, extract and salt.
Fold in the marshmallows.
Drop by heaping spoonfuls into coconut; toss to coat, then place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 1 hour or until firm.

title: steak soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Melt butter in a 16-cup kettle. Add flour, water, onion, celery and carrots.
Boil down good to make soupy paste and add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: gelatin macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cool.
Dissolve gelatin in water. Mix all ingredients with gelatin and pour into mold.
Set until firm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water and cook until forms firm ball in water.
Add peanuts and cook until sugar-syrup mixture turns light brown.
Add vanilla and butter.
Add 1 teaspoon soda (lump free) and stir fast until thoroughly dissolved.
While still foaming, pour into pan lined with aluminum foil.
Do not overstir.

title: potato-sauerkraut soup
directions: In 4-quart slow cooker, stir in all ingredients. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: banana pudding(century year old recipe)
directions: Heat milk, then add the milk to the beaten egg yolks.
Mix sugar, salt and flour; add milk and egg mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick, adding vanilla.
Place layer of wafers in bottom of bowl, then a layer of bananas, then a layer of pudding.
Continue in this manner until bowl is almost full.
Last layer should be pudding.
Top with meringue.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix flour and sugar and add to eggs.
Add margarine, flavoring and squash.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix vegetable oil and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time) and zucchini.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt; add to first mixture.
Add nuts.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Roll out crescents on nonstick baking sheet and place 1 tablespoon of chicken inside each roll. Add a heaping teaspoonful of cheese on top of chicken. Roll up, starting at the short side of the triangle. Bake 11 to 13 minutes at 350° until lightly golden in color.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine apple cider and the next 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes. Remove and discard spices.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: cracker jack
directions: Cook margarine or butter, brown sugar and Karo for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda; mix thoroughly.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir until all corn is coated.
Put in shallow pan and bake at 200° for 1 hour (stir every 15 minutes).
Add nuts if desired. This will keep crisp if put in an airtight container.

title: peanut butter chocolate cake
directions: In mixing bowl add all ingredients, except coffee, and beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in coffee (batter will be thin).
Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Cream half the sugar with the butter; the other half with the eggs.
Sift flour, meal and salt and add to the sugar and butter. Mix in all the remaining ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pastry and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry juice punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Be sure sugar and Tang are dissolved. Freeze (in milk jugs or Ziploc bags).
Serve with 1 quart ginger ale (25 punch cups), partially thaw frozen part before use.

title: pea salad
directions: In large bowl, put in layers:
lettuce, onions, cauliflower and then frozen peas.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and Parmesan cheese together and spread over salad.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Place tight lid on bowl and refrigerate 12 hours.
Stir and serve.

title: chunky spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and place in a large crock-pot.
Slice Italian sausage and pepperoni. Place in crock-pot with jars of sauce.
Add spices and heat on high until hot.
Cook for 2 hours on low heat. Serve with spaghetti noodles and *toasted French garlic bread.

title: gail's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Cut stems into small pieces. Melt margarine in skillet.
Crumble sausage into skillet; add onion.
Lightly fry and turn off.
Add stems, bread crumbs and egg; mix.
Stuff mushrooms.
Arrange in baking dish.
Dot with olive oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese or Port wine, as desired.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: walnut cheese ball
directions: Spread walnuts in shallow pan; toast at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cream together the cheeses.
Blend in salt and garlic salt.
Add green pepper and pimento; blend with cheeses and salts. Chill.
Shape in ball; roll in chopped walnuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter both sides of frozen bread and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan; cut into cubes.
Spread sausage over bread, then sprinkle with cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and mustard.
Pour over layered bread, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal; let stand for 10 minutes. Mix other ingredients in. Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut-up chicken in bite size pieces and save 1 cup of chicken broth for later use.
Spray nonstick spray in
an 8 x 8 x 3-inch casserole dish.
Place cut-up chicken in bottom of the dish.
Cover chicken with broccoli.
In a separate dish, mix together soups, lemon juice, curry powder and chicken broth.
Pour mixture over broccoli and chicken.
Cover with stuffing and brush top of stuffing with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caribbean castaway punch
directions: Stir all ingredients except ice together
in a large punch bowl. Refrigerate until cold.
Add a block of ice or ice cubes to bowl with punch. Ladle punch into glasses.

title: jule kage
directions: Scald milk; remove from heat.
Add butter, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Add to yeast which has been dissolved in water. Add eggs and 3 to 4 cups flour.
I use mixer for this step.
Mix fruit with 1 cup flour before adding to mixture.
Keep adding flour; dough should not be too stiff.
Knead well.
Place dough in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Brush tops with butter.
Remove from pans and when not quite cool, frost with confectioners frosting.
If you bring half and half cream to a boil before adding powdered sugar, the result will be better.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Add white syrup to sugar in a 1-quart dish.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add salted peanuts.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave at High 1 minute.
Add baking soda. Do not overstir.
Mix, just a little and dump on a flat pan covered with foil.
Allow to cool completely.
Remove from foil and break into pieces.

title: tuna dip
directions: Combine sour cream and seasonings.
Add tuna; mix well to break chunks of tuna.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Great with fresh cup of vegetables.

title: cherry topped cheesecake
directions: Combine cake mix with oil (reserve 1 cup cake mix for batter) and 1 egg.
Pat in bottom and up sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or two 9-inch pans for crust.

title: easy one-dish ham bake
directions: Brown meat.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, sweet basil and catsup.
Dice three slices of cheese and add to meat.
Spoon mixture into the pastry shell.
Arrange slices of tomato over meat.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Cut remaining cheese into 6 wedges.
Arrange on top of pie.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Broil 2 to 3 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Cut into six wedges to serve.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl and serve.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients in plastic bag.
Add 3 pounds chicken wings and marinate overnight.
Bake for 30 minutes or broil for 10 minutes (watch carefully).

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk, diced marshmallows and margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Continue boiling for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Do not let mixture scorch.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Beat until well blended and mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered loaf pan. Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: beef broccoli casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cook broccoli and rice.
Melt cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until the casserole is not very runny.

title: 24-hour wine omelette
directions: Butter 2 shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dishes.
Spread bread over the bottom and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with Swiss and Jack cheeses and salami.
Beat together eggs and next 6 ingredients. Pour over cheese.
Cover dishes with foil, crimping edges. Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Bring the Karo syrup and sugar to a boil; remove from heat. Add the peanut butter; stir until melted.
Pour over the Rice Krispies.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Pat down with wet hand to 1/2-inch thick.
Add the chocolate chips.
Melt in warm oven until melted.
Spread with knife.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in vegetable oil until tender.
Add soup, milk, Cheez Whiz and hominy.
Blend and bring to a boil.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1 cup crushed Fritos.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage stew
directions: Brown sausage in butter.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Let simmer on low for just a little while.
Add water and potatoes and carrots.
Salt and pepper to taste and cook until vegetables are done.
Serve over rice.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in order given and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or lightly browned on top.
The last 5 minutes, sprinkle grated cheese on top to brown lightly.

title: shrimp dish
directions: Shell shrimp, leaving tails on, then devein.
Heat all other ingredients over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Place shrimp in an ovenproof dish and pour garlic mixture over it.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with rice or over pasta.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Place onions in skillet.
Add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Cook for 20 minutes, covered.
Add onion mixture to combined beans.
Add bacon.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger surprise muffins
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Set aside.
Mix Bisquick mix in a bowl.
Set aside.
Cut cheese into small cubes and add to Bisquick.
Add salt and pepper to ground beef.
Grease muffin pan with oil.
Fill each cup half full with ground beef.
Top with Bisquick mix.
Place in oven at 350° for 5 minutes or until brown. Remove and let stand 5 to 10 minutes to cool.
Place on dish with paper towel.
Serve immediately.

title: crab salad
directions: Boil noodles.
Grate cheese.
Chop onion.
Drain and rinse peas.
Chop up crab meat.
Drain noodles and rinse in cool water. Combine all ingredients.
Add mayonnaise until desired consistency.

title: georgia's special hamburgers
directions: Mix everything well and shape into fat patties.
Grills well.

title: salsa
directions: Blend whole tomatoes and Rotel tomatoes in blender. Add lots of garlic and salt; add cilantro if desired. Serve with chips.

title: string bean gamurse
directions: Cut up cottage ham into bite size pieces.
Wash cottage ham thoroughly to remove any brine.
Place in crock-pot.
Add 4 to 5 cups of water.
Add string beans, onions, potatoes, pepper and marjoram.
Cook on high for 4 hours.
Cook on low for 2 hours. Stir occasionally, then enjoy!

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Roll boneless chicken breast in butter.
Then roll in cracker and cheese mixture . Place in baking dish and bake for 50 minutes at 350°,
first 30 minutes covered.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil and pepper.
Add to beans which have been well drained.
Add onions.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sesame chicken with cumberland sauce
directions: Coat chicken pieces with coating mix as directed on package. Place in shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and pineapple; marinate overnight.
Drain.
Add nuts and bananas; fold in whipped topping. Chill before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix 2 envelopes of dressing mix as directed.
Add the third envelope dry.
Add seasoning from remaining package number three to your taste.

title: chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine chicken and celery in bowl.
Mix salad dressing, salt, poultry seasoning, onion salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and celery; toss.
Cover; chill 2 hours.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for at least 30 minutes. Toss with other ingredients. Place in large casserole dish. Prepare white sauce (2 tablespoons butter, melted and 2 tablespoons flour). Stir until bubbly, then add 2 cups milk. Heat, stirring constantly until thick. Top with crushed corn flakes tossed with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into eighths.
Coarsely chop green onions.
Add green onions, garlic and butter to a 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion and saute for 1 minute.
Add potatoes and pour in broth.
Simmer 20 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Pour into food processor or blender and puree.
Add cream, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Chill to serve cold or reheat to serve hot.
Garnish with croutons if desired.

title: seafood quiche
directions: In bowl, mix together mayonnaise and flour, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: shepherd's dip
directions: Hollow out center of one loaf Hawaiian round bread (Shepherd's) and save for dipping.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice, pineapple, coconut, cherries and nuts. Pour into pie crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top; chill.

title: green chili chicken
directions: Rub outside of chicken with mixture of chili powder, cayenne, cumin and salt.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Add garlic, onion, chilies and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan to platter draining juices back into pan.
Skim fat from sauce in pan.
Blend together flour and water.
Stir into sauce.
Cook stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in sour cream.
Carve chicken and serve with sauce.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Mix grated cheese with salad dressing.
Spoon mixture over a canned artichoke heart, which is placed on a piece of square rye cocktail bread.
Broil until cheese bubbles.

title: marbled cheesecake deluxe(makes one 9-inch cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare chocolate crumb crust.
Stir together margarine and cocoa until smooth.
In large mixer bowl beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and flour.
Put 1 1/2 cups into medium bowl.
Beat in cocoa mixture.
Spoon half vanilla batter in pan, then half chocolate.
With metal spatula cut through batter to marble.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes, until center is set.
Cool.
Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cook, devein and slice shrimp.
Finely chop celery and onion. Mix all ingredients together and blend.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours before using.

title: microwave baked halibut
directions: In a 10-inch glass baking dish, heat butter 30 seconds.
Add mustard, parsley flakes, lemon juice and garlic powder; stir to blend.
Coat fish in sauce and arrange around sides of dish. Cook, covered, 5 to 6 minutes, rotating dish one-quarter turn halfway through cooking time.
Rest, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Freeze steak for 1 hour for easier slicing.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add garlic, salt, ginger and pepper.
Saute garlic until tender.
Add steak slices; brown lightly for 2 minutes.
Remove meat.
Add green peppers and onions, cooking for 3 minutes.
Return meat to pan along with all remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 2 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Serve over hot rice.

title: mexican cream candy
directions: Cook until soft ball stage, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts after it reaches soft ball stage.
Take off heat and have ready a pan with ice water.
Place candy pan in water and stir until stiff.
Be careful it doens't set up.
Butter two pie plates or 9 x 9-inch cake pans, depending on how thick you would like this.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan, 9 x 5-inch.
Bake 55 minutes; cool on rack.

title: ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on tortillas.
Roll tortilla tightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces. Makes 3 dozen.

title: dump salad
directions: Drain fruit well and pour into large bowl.
Add cottage cheese and stir.
Add Cool Whip and stir.
Add large package of Jell-O and stir.
Store in refrigerator.
Enjoy.
Do not make Jell-O.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrot, green pepper and medium onion together after chopping and add salt.
Let stand 15 minutes; drain well if needed.
Add sugar and cider vinegar; pour over slaw and let stand 2 hours before serving.
Store in quart jars.
Lasts several weeks. Do not use plastic.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Place
vanilla	wafer
crumbs
in
bottom of container. Stir lemonade
into ice cream and mix well.
Quickly spoon ice cream mixture on top of crumbs.
Sprinkle additional crumbs on top. Cover
and refrigerate.
(Texture of cream will change.) Various shapes
and sizes of containers may use used.
Makes 2 pies.
One (9-inch) square will make thick servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add soup, cheese and half of onions. Mix well.
Spread in a shallow baking dish.
Top with onions. Bake until hot and then boil until onion is brown.
Serve hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Stir in beaten eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add sifted flour mixture and mix together. Knead on a floured board; roll and cut as you like.
Sprinkle with colored sugars.
Bake on sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.

title: pimento cheese dip
directions: Drain
pimento	and mash fine.	Mix with other ingredients. Serve with crackers.

title: crustless potato quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
In large bowl, combine ingredients except paprika and bacon; mix well.
Pour mixture into greased pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle with bacon; bake an additional 5 minutes.
Let stand before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together; let stand until sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into apples.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into 1 (8 x 8-inch) pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Butter a nice size casserole.
Sprinkle rice in dish.
Mix soups, salt and water and pour mixture over raw rice.
Dip chicken in melted butter.
Salt pieces lightly and lay on top of soups. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: mystery salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Serves 15.

title: chuck and potato bake
directions: Trim fat from meat; place in a large baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Roast at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off fat.
Arrange potatoes around roast.

title: jim's apple pie
directions: Place sliced apple pieces into unbaked pastry shell.
Mix 6 or 8 Equal bags with brown sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Sprinkle over the sliced apples.
Squeeze the juice of one orange over the mixture and cover with pastry.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes, then reduce oven to 350°.
Bake until golden brown, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: skillet steak dinner
directions: Cut steak; dredge in flour seasoned with salt.
Place 3 or 4 carrot strips on each piece of steak.
Wrap around carrots and fasten with toothpicks.
Brown rolls slowly in shortening and add potatoes and onions.
Pour mushroom soup over all.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until soft.

title: strawberry creme cake
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Drain and save juice.
Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Cook according to directions vanilla pudding.
Pour over cake while hot.
Set aside to cool, but do not refrigerate.
Add water to drained juice.
Mix with cornstarch and cook until thick.
When cool, add strawberries to thickened juice mixture, then spread over cake and pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over strawberry mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares and top with a strawberry if desired.

title: hobo banquets
directions: Divide ground beef into four portions.
Place on squares of aluminum foil, shiny side up.
Slice potatoes and bell pepper and quarter onions.
Arrange vegetables on foil as needed for serving. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Seal foils tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: dinner in a skillet
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Shape into small balls; roll in flour.
Brown evenly in skillet.
When the meatballs are completely browned, add tomato soup and Veg-All.
Simmer at least 1 hour and more if you have time.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil whole chicken in water until done.
Debone meat when cool.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Combine all other ingredients together.
Layer in casserole dish the rice and chicken mixture and top with stuffing and butter mixture.
Spread shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts on top.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done in greased and floured pan.

title: broccoli and rice salad
directions: Cook broccoli and rice until tender.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well and chill.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: braised beef
directions: Buy an inexpensive cut of meat, either steak or roast.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch cubes.
Combine flour and seasoning in a Baggie. Coat the beef cubes.
Brown in a skillet with the Crisco.
Reserve remaining flour mixture.
Slice the onion and add with the mushrooms and can of beef broth.
Cover; let simmer for 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
Put flour mixture and water together, then add to the meat mixture until thickened to your taste.
Serve over homemade noodles.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well and store in tightly covered container.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add

title: brandy ice
directions: Pour into a chilled blender and blend quickly.
Makes 1 serving.
May be doubled.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix beans, butter, and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Do not preheat oven.
Pinto beans should be cooked like you would cook them but not seasoned with ham.
Can be baked as one pie.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: intake stew
directions: Drain intakes at power plant.
Scrape mussels, clams and oysters off walls.
Throw away the ones that smell bad.
If there are any eels laying around, you can use them also.
Next, add potatoes, carrots, peas and seaweed (optional).
Boil until dead. Drain water and add 2 to 3 cans gravy.
Simmer until gravy heats through.
Serve with nose clips.

title: taco soup
directions: In a pan, mix your hamburger, onion and taco mix until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Put all ingredients in pot; simmer until very hot.
Put cheese cubes in bowl.
Pour in hot soup and put crushed corn chips on top.

title: holiday butterhorns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar.
Stir and mix all ingredients together, reserving just enough butter to brush top of dough.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, divide dough into 3 parts.
Shape into balls.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch.
Cut circles into 12 pie-shaped cuts. Starting from large end, roll up.
Place on greased sheet and let rise uncovered for several hours.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 36 crescent shaped rolls.
Dough may be kept several days in refrigerator.
Shaped rolls may be frozen and used as needed.

title: mincemeat pie
directions: Heat together and put into crust.
Bake until crust is done.

title: cranberry mallow salad
directions: Combine and refrigerate cranberries, marshmallow and sugar. Refrigerate overnight.
Two to three hours before serving, add apples, walnuts and cream.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lahvosh roll
directions: Stir together cream cheese, artichoke hears, pimento, and oregano in a bowl.
Spread tortilla with cream cheese mixture. Arrange ham over cream cheese.
Place cheese slices in the center and lettuce leaf next to cheese.
Roll up tortilla.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain pears.
Heat 1 cup juice to boiling.
Pour over gelatin to dissolve.
Cool.
Add cream cheese and 2 tablespoons cream. Beat smooth.
Add gelatin mixture; beat until partly thickened. Fold in mashed pears and whipped cream.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: beef steak
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Roll into 3 oblong rolls.
Place in foil, shiny side in.
Cover with water, boil 1 hour.
When done, rewrap.
Drain on paper towel.

title: deep-dish chicago pizza
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat sausages and 1/4 cup water to boiling; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove cover; continue cooking, turning sausages frequently, until sausages are well browned, about 20 minutes. Remove to paper towels to drain.
With knife, slice diagonally to 1/4-inch thick slices; place in bowl.
Preheat oven to 400°. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Prepare hot roll mix as directed, but use 1 cup water and omit egg; do not let dough rise.
Pat dough onto bottom and halfway up sides of baking dish to make a stand-up edge.
In medium bowl, mix spaghetti sauce, next 5 ingredients and sliced sausage.
Sprinkle half of Mozzarella over dough in baking dish; top with spaghetti sauce mixture, Parmesan cheese and remaining Mozzarella.
Bake pizza on bottom rack of oven 25 minutes or until topping is hot and bubbly and crust is browned and crisp.
Serves 8.

title: jessie's "beam" bars
directions: Mix the sugars and flour.
Cut in butter.
Combine 2 cups of this mixture with the nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add remaining crumb mix and beat hard.
Spread over unbaked layer in pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool, then frost.
Cut into bars.

title: magic cookie bars(7 layer cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Using a glass

baking pan, melt butter in oven. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter. Use back of tablespoon to spread evenly. Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Use back of spoon to spread evenly. Sprinkle nuts over layer of milk, then peanut butter morsels, then butterscotch morsels. Last, spread coconut evenly over the top. Wet your hand with cold water and press the mixture down. Press corners down with the spoon. Bake 25-30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Cut into squares. Store loosely covered at room temperature. While it's still hot, take and knife and loosen sides.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: On a sheet of aluminum foil, place 1/2 acorn squash.
Fill with 1 tablespoon each of butter and brown sugar.
Seal foil.
Bake in 425° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corned beef stew
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes and boil until tender.
Add corned beef, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Cut up onion and add to mixture.
Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes or until onion is tender. Delicious with fried cornbread.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Beat together egg yolks, lemon juice, lemon rind and margarine with a rotary beater.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend into yolk mixture on low speed.
Pour mixture into 8-inch square baking pan.
Set in a pan of hot water.

title: debbie's lemon chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chicken).
Place chicken in heavy plastic bag (or bowl/container) and pour marinade over chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or cook on grill until chicken is done.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Combine sour cream and seasonings.
Coat chicken breasts with it.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll chicken in cup of crumbs.

title: chocolate peanut butter dessert
directions: Mix 1/4 cup peanut butter with 1/4 cup skim milk. Gently stir in whipped topping. Pour 4 cups milk into large glass bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat 2 minutes or until well blended. Spread crushed graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon pudding on top of crumbs and carefully spread over pan. Slice bananas on top of pudding. Layer Cool Whip mixture on top. Makes 12 servings. Each serving contains 176 calories and 5.8 g fat.

title: mother's white potato cake
directions: Mix together first three ingredients while potatoes are hot. Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Grease pan and pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie #2
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hearty taco slices
directions: In a medium bowl, combine refried beans, 1/4 cup salsa, 1/2 cup cheese and olives; set aside.
Slice loaf in half horizontally; remove soft insides, leaving 1-inch thick shell.
Spread bean mixture over bottom half of loaf; set aside.

title: frozen strawberry jam
directions: Thaw frozen strawberries.
Put through food mill or mush.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. When sugar has dissolved, add liquid fruit pectin.
Stir 3 minutes.
Ladle in hot sterilized jar or clean freezer container. Cover and let stand 24 hours or until set.
Seal with paraffin. Store up to 6 weeks in refrigerator or 1 year in the freezer. Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until all water is absorbed.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar; add salt, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well together.
Put in frozen pie crust; scatter broken pecan pieces over top and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
For richer pie, use brown sugar and butter instead of coconut; use chopped pecans.
It's delicious.

title: devil dogs
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, add cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt to flour.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Put together with cream filling between.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain the Fiesta mix, then mix all together.
Put topping on top and cook for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: taco hot dish
directions: Saute margarine, onion and green pepper.
Brown beef and drain off fat.
Add to sauteed vegetables.
Stir in mushroom soup, tomato paste, salt, oregano and chili powder.
Place half of Doritos on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, then pour meat mixture on top of Doritos.
Add Colby cheese.
On top of cheese, add rest of Doritos.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pound cake(sugar free)
directions: Combine
flour,
soda,	salt
and
apple pie spice in a large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed. Beat together oil, Sweet 'N Low, eggs and vanilla until thoroughly combined. Gradually beat
in
flour mixture. Fold in apples, pecans and raisins. Pour into
a
greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at
for 1	hour
and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool cake in pan 10 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Cut up onion (chopped). Mix in with ground beef and cook until onions are soft and beef is brown. In a large pot, mix chili beans, tomato juice and ground beef mixture; add chili mix. Cook until hot. Serves 5.

title: real hungarian goulash
directions: Mix salt, pepper, small amount of flour (4 tablespoons) and paprika.
Dredge beef; shake off excess.
Saute in hot bacon fat until lightly browned.
Add chopped onion, garlic and green pepper.
Stir to prevent sticking until onion glazes.
Add tomatoes, parsley and water.
Cover and cook slowly 2 hours.
Cook noodles or spaghetti.
Add to the meat mixture 10 minutes before serving.
Good for crock-pot simmering.

title: crabbies hors d'oeuvres
directions: *Shrimp, ham or any other product may be substituted.

title: best gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Measure and sift dry ingredients.
Mix molasses with hot water.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid.
Beat after each addition. Bake in paper-lined 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Makes 16 portions.

title: deer stew
directions: Marinate meat in soy sauce for about 1 hour.
Save soy sauce for later.
Flour meat and brown in 1 inch of oil; drain on paper towel.
Put browned meat in stew pot or Dutch oven.
Add soy sauce and vegetables and fill pot with enough water to have about 2 or 3 inches above the ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring about every 10 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Pepper to taste.
Stew should get thick like gravy.
Serve with crackers.
Serves about 4 to 6.

title: copper pennies(carrot salad)
directions: Marinate carrots, onion and green pepper in tomato soup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand overnight.

title: lemon coconut cake
directions: Mix well the dry ingredients.
Pour in beaten eggs, corn oil and water; beat until smooth.
Pour in 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake 55 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Run knife here and there to run out air bubbles.
Set a few minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: After mixing dry ingredients, mix in butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake on top rack at 350° for 15 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: delores' winter salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper. Boil. Rinse kraut very well in colander in cold water.
Drain well.
Put in bowl.
Pour over hot mixture. Add remaining and chill well.

title: granny goo
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and one egg.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining eggs and cream cheese with sugar. Pour this over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: de-de's spinach salad
directions: Remove and discard spinach stems.
Rinse leaves. Drain and pat dry.
Tear into bite size pieces and arrange in a salad bowl. Evenly layer cucumber slices, radishes, green onions and eggs on top of spinach. Spread dressing over top.
Do not mix. Cover and chill up to 24 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon and peanuts.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: lacy layer oven meal
directions: Place ingredients
in
2 1/2-quart baking dish in order given. Sprinkle
each
layer
with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with soda cracker
crumbs.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: paula's sausage cheese dip
directions: Melt cheeses in top of double boiler.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard, onion flakes, hot sauce, chili powder and garlic powder.
Slowly add whipping cream to mixture, stirring constantly.
When all is dissolved and smooth, add sausage.
Serve in chafing dish hot with Tostitos chips.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate before serving.

title: tiramisu
directions: In top of double boiler, beat together egg yolks and sugar until lemon yellow.
Bring water to boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove mixture from heat. Stir in Mascarpone, beating well.
Let cool to room temperature. Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold into the egg and cheese mixture.
Combine liqueur with coffee and use this mixture to brush ladyfingers until they are well saturated, but not falling apart.
Line sides and bottom of a 3-quart souffle dish or any straight-sided dish with 36 of the ladyfingers.
(I have used a flat baking dish with good results; just cut the ladyfingers in half lengthwise.)
Pour in half the filling.
Layer remaining ladyfingers on top.
Cover with remaining filling. Smooth the top with spatula.
Combine sugar and cocoa to taste and sprinkle on top.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Stir, then let sherbet melt.

title: triple treat
directions: Mix together flour, butter and chopped nuts.
Spread in pan. Bake
minutes
at 375° or until light golden.
Blend cheese and
sugar;
add
Cool
Whip.
Spread
on top of cooled crust. Beat instant pudding until thick.
Put on top of cream cheese layer.
Add
some chopped nuts and Cool Whip;
sprinkle nuts. Chill.

title: buttered carrots
directions: Wash carrots and peel.
Cut in squares.
Add 3 tablespoons of butter.
Have low fire and add 1/2 cup of water.
Let cook slow, stirring so carrots won't burn.
If you want them sweetened, add sugar to taste.

title: val's zesty dip
directions: Brown hamburger and mix all ingredients together in crock-pot and simmer until cheese is melted.

title: tomato salad
directions: Chop onion very fine.
Squeeze lemons into mixing bowl.
Add onion and let stand.
Cut tomatoes into small chunks.
Cut cilantro very fine.
Combine tomatoes, cilantro and the rest of the ingredients with the onion and lemon juice.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients 1 to 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into prepared loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 28 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Makes about 7 mini loaves.

title: chipmunks (mom's)
directions: Combine boiling water and dates; let cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Sift cocoa, flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients and date mixture into the creamed ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread flat in pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press crescent rolls into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes; let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and dip.
Mix together and spread over cooled rolls. Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into squares.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix well and
add salad oil, eggs, water and pumpkin. Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Precook pie shells as label instructs.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Add water.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and is bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in package dry jello.
After dissolved, add berries and pour into 2 pie shells.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, until jello is set.
Add whipped topping and enjoy.
Peaches may be substituted and add peach jello.

title: grape salad
directions: Amount of salad depends on the amount you want.
One pound of each variety of grapes, wash and separate.
Stir in sour cream and sugar (this can be determined by how sweet you want, I use 2 tablespoons).
Add nuts and stir.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set either overnight or at least 4 hours.
Do not add water to Jell-O, just put the dry Jell-O in with the other ingredients.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Mix together; put in heavy pan and cover.
Bake in 359° oven for 1 hour.
Stir frequently.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rice con queso
directions: Lightly spray 1 1/2-quart casserole with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake potatoes 1 hour or until fork-tender.
Cool until potatoes can be handled.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp leaving 1/4 to 1/2-inch shell. Position oven rack 4 to 6 inches from heat source.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses, then add hot water.
Add dry ingredients using enough flour to make a stiff dough so you
can
roll
out
cookies
(about 4 cups). Bake in 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: quickie lunch
directions: Break saimin and
boil.
Drain.
Empty	can of sardines in frying pan;
heat.	Add
saimin;
stir
well, breaking sardines. Add onions.
Packet
of saimin seasoning may be added, if you want more taste.

title: pickled cucumbers
directions: Mix well and pour over cucumbers.
Store in plastic container.

title: million dollar pie(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Mix thoroughly. Pour into 3 (8-inch) graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Put cake in two 9-inch round cake pans.
When cake is done and cooled completely, take a punch bowl and put almost 1/4 the tub of Cool Whip on bottom.
Put one layer of cake on top of Cool Whip; add 1 can pie filling to layer of cake.
Put enough Cool Whip to cover; then sprinkle 1/2 cup walnuts.
Repeat procedure again.

title: peanut soup
directions: Heat bouillon and peanut butter together in a pan slowly, stirring until the peanut butter is dissolved.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add onions and tomatoes; simmer until onions are soft. Pour into bowls and sprinkle sparingly with hot pepper.
Serves 4.

title: fat free peaches and cream cheese cake
directions: Combine and beat for 2 minutes; flour baking powder, salt, margarine, egg whites, milk and pudding. Pour into 8 x 13-inch baking dish or big pie plate; greased.
Drain peaches; place fruit over batter.
Beat together for 2 minutes cream cheese, 1/2 cup of sugar and 3 tablespoons of peach juice you reserved.
Spoon over fruit within 1 inch of sides.
Sprinkle a mixture of 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Filling will appear soft, but will set as it chills.
Chill well.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 1/2 sticks oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Drain the peaches and add enough water to the juice to make 3 cups. Dissolve the sugar in the juice and add with the peaches into the melted oleo.

title: orange cake
directions: Combine all ingredients at medium speed for 3 minutes. Grease, but not flour, angel food pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add sugar to taste. Sprinkle with coconut flakes. Chill.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Thaw fish; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place fish in greased 1-quart casserole.
Pour milk over fillets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Remove from oven; drain off and reserve milk.
Melt butter in skillet; stir and blend in flour.
Gradually add reserved milk; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture has thickened.
Add mustard, seasoned salt, lemon juice and mix well. Pour sauce over fillets in baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes.
Dust lightly with paprika before serving.
Serves 4.
Contains 226 calories per serving.

title: chili rellenos quiche
directions: Beat eggs, onion, garlic and 1 teaspoon salt together.
Pour 1/2 egg mix into crust.
Layer:
chili, cheese, chili and eggs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake according to directions (in any size pan).
Cut into cubes.
Make pudding according to directions on package.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Scrub and cook potatoes; drain, peel and slice while hot.
Add chopped eggs.
Fry bacon and onion until a delicate brown. Strain, reserving bacon fat.
Add onion and bacon to the potato mixture; toss lightly.
Add bacon fat slowly to beaten egg, beating well.
Add vinegar and salt; pour over potatoes.
Mix lightly to blend well.
Heat in double boiler.
Serve hot, garnished with salad greens.
Sliced celery root may be added. Serves 6.

title: taco casserole
directions: Combine Bisquick, refried beans and water; press in bottom of glass baking dish.
Brown hamburger.
Drain and let cool a bit. Pour over bean/Bisquick mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Remove and cover with cheese.
Melt cheese.
Then cover with shredded lettuce, tomato and onions.

title: dilly cucumbers
directions: Beat together oil and vinegar.
Stir in dill, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over sliced cucumbers.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Simmer tomato juice, bay leaf, onions and salt together for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice.
Strain mixture and add hot tomato juice.
Makes 2 cups.
Pour over lemon Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill.
Add celery.

title: daddy's favorite oyster stew
directions: Melt butter. Add oysters (in their liquor) and cook 8 minutes or until edges curl. Add milk and seasonings and heat slowly to the boiling point, but do not boil.
Pour into soup bowls and sprinkle with parsley. Serve at once with oyster crackers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potatoes poupon
directions: In a medium saucepan, over medium heat, cook shallots in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in cream, mustard and remaining butter or margarine.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Reduce heat to low; add 1/2 cup shredded cheese and basil, stirring until cheese melts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oblong pan.
Pour can of peaches on top of the melted butter.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together in a bowl, then pour mixture on top of peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325°, or until lightly browned.

title: rosemary-grilled lamb chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Place chops in a large shallow dish.
Combine wine and next 6 ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over chops; cover and refrigerate 2 hours, turning occasionally.

title: cabbage and potato soup(maribeth's specialty)
directions: In a pot, put broth, potatoes and cabbage.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, melt butter.
Add leeks; stir in flour and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 1 cup milk to pot. Add leeks and all remaining ingredients from the skillet and all other ingredients to the pot.
Add remaining milk.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Combine melted margarine and 1/4 cup fruit sweetener and spread evenly in 9-inch square or round pan.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup of the juice.
Arrange pineapple rings in pan. Arrange nuts around pineapple.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 10-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: deleeta bites
directions: Mix well butter, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour and nuts.
Chill.
Shape into marble sized balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15-17 minutes.
Roll gently in powdered sugar.
Cool, sugar again.
Makes 50.

title: midnight breakfast eggs
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Line with cheese, then sausage, then onion and mushrooms.
Pour eggs over.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued bass rhythm sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken; mix well.
Add chicken; stir until coated.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours, spooning marinade over chicken occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade; reserve marinade.
Place chicken in wire broiling basket.
Grill over low coals for 25 minutes, basting with reserved marinade occasionally.
Turn; grill for 20 minutes longer, or until tender, basting with marinade occasionally.
Chicken may be marinated overnight in refrigerator, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine 1 c. sugar and cornstarch in a medium size thick bottom pan.
Separate egg from yolks and set white aside.
Add the egg yolks to the sugar mixture and slowly add the milk until combined and not lumpy.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add butter one piece at a time, stirring until melted.
Add vanilla and 1/2 c. coconut.
Stir well.
Place filling in baked pie shell.
In a small bowl, mix 7 Tbsp. sugar with confectioners sugar and stir well.
Place reserved egg white in another mixing bowl.
Add a pinch of salt.
Beat on medium low until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and increase speed to medium high.
When soft peaks form, begin adding sugar gradually.
Beat until firm (but not dry) peaks form.
Add vanilla and beat on high for about 30 seconds.
Place meringue on top of filling.
Make sure that meringue covers entire filling area and seals to crust.
Sprinkle remaining 2 Tbsp. coconut over meringue.
Bake at 350 degrees until meringue is lightly browned (about 8 minutes).
Cool at room temperature, then refrigerate.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: grilled three-cheese sandwiches
directions: Process cottage cheese in food processor until smooth.
Mix cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, celery, raisins and Parmesan cheese.
Spread evenly on three pieces of the bread, topping with the remaining bread.
Heat in skillet until cheese is melted. Makes 3 sandwiches.

title: easy tortoni
directions: Combine pudding, milk and sugar in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until it comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat and cover with wax paper.
Chill.
Beat pudding; add extract and cherries. Fold whip cream into pudding.
Pour into cups; top with coconut and freeze until firm.

title: chili con carne
directions: Wash beans.
Cover with cold water and let stand, covered, overnight.
Next day, drain.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet.
Cook noodles in salted water. Mix all ingredients lightly.
Place in large casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and cheese, grated.
Good eaten hot or cold.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Add the flour, baking powder and soda.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: no bake brownies
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate and butter.
In large bowl, combine crumbs and nuts.
Stir in milk and vanilla; add chocolate mix.
Pour in greased 12 x 8-inch dish.
Let stand at room temperature 2 hours.
Yields 24.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, beaten slightly.
Add flour and flavoring.
Beat about 10 minutes with mixer after all is mixed.
Pour into floured tube pan and place in cold oven. Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salad supreme
directions: Step 1:
Mix Jell-O as directed.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish and allow to almost congealed.
Then add pineapple and return to refrigerator.

title: chocolate cake using cocoa
directions: Cream first two ingredients and set aside.
Cook next 3 ingredients and cool.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add eggs, etc.
Pour
into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coffee ice cream pie
directions: Crush cookies in blender; mix with melted butter to form a crust.
Press into a 10-inch pan and freeze.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs with a fork to mix lightly.
Add mashed bananas, vanilla, vegetable oil, Bisquick mix, sugar and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan about 5 minutes.
Loosen edges; cool on rack.

title: heath bars
directions: Butter one cookie sheet and cover bottom with crackers.
Melt margarine and add powdered sugar.
Boil margarine and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour this over the crackers carefully covering all. Bake at 400° for exactly 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top as soon as removed from oven.
When chips melt, spread gently to cover tops of all crackers.
Cool, then cut or break into serving pieces.
(Sometimes this does better if refrigerated for awhile before cutting.)

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix and freeze until mushy.
Stir, then freeze 12 hours. Takes 6 hours to thaw.
Should be served "slushy."
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.
Serves 25.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat butter and olive oil in a large skillet.
Add shrimp and saute on both sides until done, about 5 minutes.
Pour off pan drippings into small saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over high heat 1 minute.
Pour sauce over shrimp.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: chocolate cream raspberry tart(low fat and low calorie)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and stir well.
Press mixture into bottom and up the sides of 11-inch round removable-bottom tart pan.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: mint puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating after each addition.
Add mint chocolate chips.
Add several drops of green food coloring.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 375° and turn off heat.
Put puffs into oven and leave overnight.

title: corn and beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain fat from beef.
Mix with remaining ingredients and put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: poached pears
directions: Cut pears.
Put all in a pot.
Boil 20 minutes.
Serve over ice cream.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Skin and wash chicken breasts.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: swedish snowballs
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the oats, sugar, cocoa, cold coffee and vanilla.
Add 1 stick margarine (melted); blend well.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: andrea's apple bake
directions: Slice apples into a baking dish; sprinkle with dry gelatin. Mix sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over the gelatin.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put ingredients in a casserole dish in the order listed. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Easy and delicious!

title: macaroni and tomato
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
In skillet, brown onion (diced) with bacon pieces.
Mix with macaroni, tomatoes, soup, salt, pepper, butter and sugar.
Add bacon and onion after draining any excess grease.

title: simple sandwich spread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste, put on bread and
. . . . surprise!

title: rick's peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: turkey stuffing(serves 8)
directions: Fry sausage in large skillet on moderate heat; break in very small pieces.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add nuts and raisins; mix well.
Simmer for 30 minutes over low heat.
Add water if needed.
Add sausage and continue to simmer for another 30 minutes.
Allow to cool for 15 minutes.
Heat 2 cans of turkey gravy in another saucepan.

title: meatball potato casserole
directions: To make meatballs:
Mix well ground beef, crumbs, onion and egg.
Add desired amount of salt and pepper.
Shape into small meatballs.
Fry meatballs in oil until brown.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add milk and coconut; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix juices.
Pour in large punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale in bowl.
Spoon scoops of sherbet on top.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, add condensed milk, lime juice and beat until thick.
Beat 1 egg white until stiff.
Fold into first mixture. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker and vanilla wafer crumbs, sugar and butter until well combined.
Spray 10-inch spring-form pan with non-stick cooking spray.
Press crumb mixture on bottom and up sides of pan. Refrigerate.

title: grilled radicchio lettuce
directions: Trim the radicchio and discard the root.
Cut into quarters lengthwise.
Coat a flat top grill with the oil and heat until very hot.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add water, vinegar, catsup and chili powder.
Simmer 30 minutes.
(If you want it seasoned to be hotter, add more chili powder.)

title: anne's chicken(serves 6 main dishes)
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Brush with melted Move Over butter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with the Italian salad dressing mix. Cover and cook on low in the crock-pot for 6 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown hamburger and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer.
Boil spaghetti noodles for 7 to 10 minutes, then drain.
Stir in egg, butter and Parmesan cheese.
Spread in deep dish pie pan to form crust. Spread cottage cheese next.
Layer spaghetti, hamburger and sauce over cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese; bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes to melt cheese.

title: diabetic banana cookies
directions: Mix Sweet 'N Low and eggs.
Beat well.
Add oil and milk. Add bananas.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture. Drop on Pam-sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Blend butter, sugar and egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix well and add pecans.
Spread in 10 3/4 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch or 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Bake in moderate 350° oven until firm and light brown and the cookies have pulled away slightly from pan.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: phyllis' blueberry pie
directions: Mix flour and pecans; add melted butter.
Mix thoroughly. Press into pie plate and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix 1 cup berries with 1/2 cup water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil and let full boil for 1 minute.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to boiling blueberries.
Cook until "fixed".
Add 3 cups berries; mix well.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: ring cookies
directions: Roll dough out to
about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in strips and form rings.
Bake 12 minutes
at
May
add
red
or green food coloring to dough to make different colored rings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut watermelon in shape of basket and flute edges.
Scoop out middle and save.
Add fruit cocktail and cut pieces of watermelon. Add cherries for color and flavor.
This makes a very fine center decoration.

title: strawberry-rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Make Crunch Topping.

title: ham and cheese pasta salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables and pasta as directed on package until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; toss to coat.
Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates, if desired.
Yields 4 (1-cup) servings.

title: jo's baked corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 2 quart casserole.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Bone and skin cooked chicken breasts; cut chicken into chunks. Prepare rice as directed on package; add to chicken.
Add mushrooms, mushroom soup and onion.
Put mixture in a casserole dish.
Pour Cheddar cheese soup on top; sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add everything else.
If this isn't a little soupy, add milk.
Put in oven until hot.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored. Add milk and beat well. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; gently fold into flour. Dip apple slices in batter. Fry in hot butter until golden brown and tender, turning once. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain all the beans.
Brown ground beef, diced bacon and onion; drain.
In large pot, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes.
(This can also be baked in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.)
You may want to leave some liquid otherwise the beans may become too dry.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread into tortillas and roll up. Cut crossways and serve.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Mix with cold pack cheese, onion and sauce.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: recipe of life
directions: Mix these thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little gifts of love.

Fold in 4 cups of prayer and raise the texture to great heights of Christian living. After pouring all this into your daily life, bake well with the heat of human kindness and thankfulness to our Lord, Jesus Christ. Serve with a smile.

title: miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend throughly.
Pour into a 10-inch pie plate that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
A crust will form on the bottom, pie filling in the center and coconut topping above.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by a scant teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: beer-cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables until cooked, but not brown. Blend in flour, dry mustard and chicken stock; cook for 5 minutes. Blend in Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese and beer. Simmer 20 minutes. Season and serve with French bread and tossed salad. Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Add pepper to chicken breasts.
Wrap slice of bacon around each piece of chicken.
Place layer of dried beef (not corned beef) in bottom of baking dish.
Arrange bacon wrapped chicken on beef slices.
Cover with mixture of chicken soup, sour cream and cream cheese.
Cover pan tightly with foil. Place in a 325° oven for 2 hours.
When tender, remove foil and let brown slightly. Serve on bed of hot rice.
Suitable for freezing.

title: cheeseburger quiche
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain. Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in greased 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Make sure mixture is smooth, no lumps.
Pour on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Take out of oven and top with sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven and bake 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes and slice.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters and save liquid.
Place butter, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and cream into oyster liquid.
Set aside. Layer crumbs and oysters in a casserole dish and pour liquid over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Mix butter, milk and sugar.
Boil 10 minutes or until syrupy. Mix in marshmallows and vanilla.
Remove from stove and add coconut.
Let cool.
Spread over cake already prepared by the directions on the box.
Be sure cake is cool.

title: corned beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender. Salt to taste. Drain and add corned beef, cheese, onion, soup and milk. Pour into buttered casserole and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes or until it starts to bubble through crumbs.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add the eggs, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well. Stir in the oats, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix together and put in greased loaf pan.
Spread more ketchup over top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: new orleans red beans and rice
directions: In Dutch oven, mix together onion, kidney beans, sausage, water, garlic, bay leaves, pepper, cayenne and salt.
Bring this to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat to low; simmer for 30 to 40 minutes until beans start to fall apart.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine juice from pineapple, broth, lemon juice, green pepper and onion.
Arrange pork chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and thyme.
Pour liquid around pork chops.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes at 425°.
Stir jelly into pan liquid.
Turn chops and bake 10 minutes more. Combine cornstarch and water; stir into pan liquid.
Top each chop with a slice of pineapple.
Lower oven to 350° and bake for 10 minutes.

title: almond butter toffee
directions: In a cold electric skillet or similar skillet, place butter. Set at 350° to 375°.
As butter melts, add sugar, stirring constantly until mixture bubbles on the sides.
Add cream of tartar and then almonds.
Stir constantly until caramel colored, about 12 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add Miracle Whip (more if needed) and salt and pepper to taste.

title: grandma's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice and measure cucumbers.
Dump into large pan(s) (turkey roasting pan(s) work well).
Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves. Add salt. Cover with ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain thoroughly. Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat. Pour mixture over drained cucumber mix.
Heat, mixing frequently (cover for quicker heating); do not boil.
Ladle into sterile quart jars.
Place in boiling water bath.
Process for 6 minutes. Makes 7 to 8 quarts.

title: crisp dilled beans
directions: Stem green
beans and pack uniformly in hot, sterilized jars. To each
pint,
add
teaspoon	red pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1
head
dill.
Heat together water, salt and vinegar.
Bring to boil;
pour over beans.
Seal at once.
Process in boiling water bath
for 5 minutes at 212°.
Makes 4 pints. Serve chilled.

title: prune spice cake
directions: In mixer bowl, sift together first 8 ingredients.
Add oil, 1/2 cup cold water, prunes, egg and vanilla.
Blend and then beat 1 minute at medium speed of electric mixer.
Turn batter into a greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle nuts atop batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: mock pierogi casserole
directions: Cook elbow macaroni 10 to 12 minutes and drain.
Saute onion in butter until soft.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half the macaroni, potatoes, the cheese, then rest of the macaroni.
Pour sauteed butter and onion over top.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Great way to use leftover mashed potatoes.

title: bread machine italian bread
directions: Put water in bread machine; add olive oil, sugar and salt. Add bread flour, then dry yeast.
Bake on regular white bread setting at light or medium.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Blend oats, baking soda and choice of one Stir-In; set aside. In a large bowl, mix peanut butter, butter and sugar until smooth. Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Add oats mixture and blend well.
Drop dough from ice cream scoops or 1/4 cup measure several inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on a cookie sheet 5 minutes and remove to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Mix all other ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Add the noodles and fold in to mix well. Microwave on High for 5 to 10 minutes (depending on wattage) or bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:
serves 6.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Add taco seasoning to drained browned beef; add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Heat through.
Cover bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Pour beef mixture over tortillas.
Place a layer of tortillas over meat mixture and set aside.
Combine cheeses and egg; pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle rows of Cheddar cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, green onions and olives across center of casserole.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Beat until creamy and add other ingredients.
Separate and clean celery.
Cut into 3-inch long pieces.
Stuff celery with mixture.
Refrigerate until served.

title: 5-grain pumpernickel bread
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in warm water, stir into cooled mixture. Gradually add wheat flour to form dough.
Knead on heavily floured surface until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Cover, let rise in warm place until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Divide in half, shape into 12 to 14-inch loaves and place on large greased cookie sheets. Cover, let rise 45 to 60 minutes.
Dough may not double in size. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until a deep golden brown.

title: sweet potatoes with cider and brown sugar
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the potatoes, cider, brown sugar, 6 tablespoons of the butter and the cinnamon stick.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Reduce the heat to a simmer, partially cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until the potatoes are tender (45 minutes).
Let cool slightly.
Remove the cinnamon stick and puree the potatoes in batches.
Transfer to an ovenproof serving dish.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Dot the potatoes with the remaining butter.
Cover with foil and bake, stirring once or twice, for about 20 minutes, until steaming.
Remove the foil and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: ranch mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes.
Stir in dry salad dressing mix. Add butter or margarine if desired.
Serves 4-6.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve the gelatine in 1/4 cup water.
Bring soup to boil in double boiler.
Dissolve cream cheese in soup.
Add gelatine, mayonnaise, celery, onion, salt and pepper.

title: reese's bars
directions: Putting margarine in last, mix graham crackers, margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Spread in jelly roll pan.
Melt chocolate and spread over above mix.
Let cool.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: raisin-bran muffins
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix will keep in refrigerator up to three weeks.
Makes three dozen.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute garlic and butter over medium heat.
Add shrimp and saute until pink.
Sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning.
Squeeze lemon over shrimp.
Add 1/3 can of chicken broth.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Cook rice with the rest of the broth.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach thoroughly and squeeze dry.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased baking dish (or Pam).
Top with seasoned crushed croutons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Rub roast with oil and rub in salt and pepper all over the surface.
