Cover in a deep roasting pan and bake 1 hour at 350°. Remove from oven, turn roast over and mix remaining ingredients and pour over roast.
Cover again and return to oven.
Continue baking for 1 1/2 hours more.
Remove from oven, uncover and let stand 15 minutes before slicing and serving.

title: nut cups
directions: Mix well and place 1 teaspoon filling in each cup.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Should make the filling after the dough is chilled.

title: 100 dollar cake(a favorite of my mother)
directions: Mix butter and sugar well; add beaten eggs and melted chocolate.
Add flour and milk a little at a time, then nuts and vanilla.
This makes a runny batter for three layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make a cream sauce with the margarine, milk and flour.
Lay sliced potatoes in baking pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover with cream sauce.
Repeat
with another layer.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° until tender.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a skillet, add butter, pimento, green pepper and onion. Cook for 10 minutes.
Add flour and mix well.
Mix rest of ingredients together and add first mixture.
Pour in casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Crumble potato chips on top and bake until brown.

title: kathryn pecans
directions: Whip egg white until stiff.
Add sugar and mix.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Fold in pecans and put on buttered cookie pan.
Cook at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-fat cheese potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes in water until tender. Drain. Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine in processor bowl or blender the cottage cheese, sour cream, flour, salt, pepper and garlic. Blend until smooth. Add mixture to cheese and onion.
Stir gently.
In small bowl, combine cornflake crumbs and margarine. Mix well. Sprinkle over the potatoes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk.
In 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole melt butter.
Pour in batter.
Sprinkle evenly with berries.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until top is lightly browned.

title: sunny lemon soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Reduce heat slightly and simmer until reduced to about 3 cups.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice. In separate bowl, combine water, egg and 1/2 cup of the cooled chicken broth.
Slowly pour back into remaining broth, stirring constantly.
Add wine, rice and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat, 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture just begins to boil. Remove from heat immediately.
Garnish with onion and lemon slices.

title: chocolate chip dessert
directions: Place vanilla wafers on bottom of sheet cake pan.
Melt chips, marshmallows and milk.
Place slices of ice cream on wafers.
Pour some mixture, another layer of wafers and ice cream, etc.
Crumble some wafers on top.
Place in freezer.

title: chocolate chip cookies(makes 36 cookies)
directions: Cream butter, salt, vanilla and sugars together.
Dissolve baking soda in small amount of hot water and add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add eggs and mix; add flour and mix well.
Fold in pecans, then chocolate.
Don't overmix chocolate.

title: goulash
directions: Put 2 tablespoons grease in frying pan.
Add onion and green pepper.
When cooked medium-well, add ground beef, salt, pepper and garlic.
Brown meat.
Add tomato soup and can of water.
Let simmer until liquid is gone.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine peas, cashews, celery, onion and bacon.
Add sour cream and toss to coat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Cover and chill well before serving.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: peanut buster dessert
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Then place ice cream over crumbs.
Pour the jar of hot chocolate sauce over ice cream and layer the peanuts.
Next put Cool Whip on and sprinkle a few cookie crumbs on top of the Cool Whip (then freeze).
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in medium bowl. Add milk, oil and egg.
Stir until just blended.
Stir in chips, nuts, cherries and orange peel.
Fill greased or lined muffin cups 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Chop the cauliflower and broccoli.
Add onions.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetables.
Chill at least overnight or longer.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: "bilodi" copper pennies
directions: Bring soup, vinegar and sugar to boil and pour over vegetables.
Mix well; chill.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
This can be used as salad over lettuce leaf.
Makes 6 cups.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: In a large bowl, place wine, meat, green peppers, celery, onion and beans.
Soak these overnight.
The following day, empty this into a large cooking pot.
Fill pot half way with water. Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 hours or until beans and meat are tender.
Add salt and pepper to desired taste.
Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meats slowly.
Drain off grease.	Add next 6 ingredients to meat.
Simmer until thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles until tender.	Drain.	Rinse in cold water.
For lasagna combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Place 1/2 of noodles.
Add 1/2 mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat mixture. Repeat layer.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make a paste of cocoa and coloring. Set aside. Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Then add paste and mix together. Then sift flour 3 times with salt. Then alternate with buttermilk. Add vanilla. Mix well. Mix vinegar and soda on the side. Then add to cake dough. Cook in layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eva's chopped liver appetizer
directions: In separate pans, saute liver and onions in small amount of olive oil.
Set aside to cool.
Then feed all ingredients through a food grinder two times.
Add salt and pepper to taste and mix with mayonnaise.
(Add more mayonnaise, if needed, to reach a spreadable consistency.)
Delicious when spread on crackers or rye bread.
May serve on bed of lettuce as an appetizer or use as a sandwich filling with your favorite bread.

title: basil shrimp and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat oil (Crisco) in large skillet on medium heat.
Add shrimp.
Stir-fry until shrimp are pink (4 minutes).
Remove to a dish.
Add all vegetables, except green onions.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender.

title: modeling dough
directions: Make dashi.
Cut tofu into 1/2-inch cubes.
Pour boiling water over thin, deep fried tofu to remove excess oil; cut in half lengthwise and cut each piece into 1/2-inch strips.
Dissolve miso paste by stirring in a small amount of dashi broth bit by bit.

title: chicken wings(bahamian style)
directions: Cut off wing tips and discard.
Disjoint each wing.
Bake wings on broiler rack.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes, turning once.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Roll each chicken breast with 1/2 bacon strip.
Place chipped beef, pulled apart, on bottom of baking dish.
Place breasts over beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered. (Although, if in oven for a long time, baste occasionally or cover with foil.)
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: mary alyce's fluffy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and milk in top of double boiler. Cook over hot water for 45 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir in sugar, margarine and a pinch of salt. Beat the egg yolks.
Add a little of the hot mixture to yolks, then stir this into the rice mixture. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold into rice mixture.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onion; add meat and brown.
Add soups, chiles and enchilada sauce and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Line baking dish with crushed Doritos.
Layer with 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 Cheddar cheese, other 1/2 meat mixture and 1/2 cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with crushed Doritos; serve.

title: spinach soup
directions: Use a blender.
If spinach is fresh, clean and wash it and remove tough stems.
Feed 1/3 of the spinach into blender with 1/4 cup water.
Cover.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into saucepan. Repeat until all spinach is blended.
Add onion, salt, nutmeg, chicken mix and remaining water.
Cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except buttered bread crumbs.
Place in a well-greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add dates, nuts and eggs (beaten light).
Bake at 375° in as thin a sheet as it will spread for approximately 15 minutes.
Cut in small squares.

title: eclairs
directions: Heat to boiling point in saucepan the water and butter.
Stir in flour all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves the pan and forms into a ball.
Beat in one egg at a time. Beat mixture until smooth and velvety.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O; add strawberries.
Chill until partially set and pour over the ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: meatza pizza
directions: Mix meat with bread crumbs, garlic salt and milk.
Spread into 9-inch pie pan smoothly and push up on sides.
Spread tomato paste over top, then mushrooms, Cheddar cheese, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and flour; mix well. Add egg and milk. Blend into flour mixture. Melt butter in baking dish (8 in. to 9 in. pan). Add flour mixture. Do not stir. Add 1 cup sugar to diced rhubarb. Drop by spoonfuls on top of flour mixture (do not stir). Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: sandy's waldorf salad
directions: Cut apples into bite size pieces and add all of the rest of ingredients.
Use about 1/4 cup of the pineapple juice along with the mayonnaise to coat apples; chill.

title: chewies
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar, then eggs.
Next, add vanilla, now flour.
Mix in nuts.
Pour in ungreased, oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick or straw comes out clean.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake and slightly cool.
Poke holes in top with pencil. Dribble condensed milk and caramel sauce (mixed together) over cake.
Let stand one hour.
Spread Cool Whip over cake. Sprinkle top with crushed Heath bars.

title: 5 pounds fudge candy
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chips, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into a waxed paper pan.
When set, cut into small pieces.

title: mcbreakfast casserole
directions: Fry bacon and crumble into bacon bits.
Layer apples, bacon and cheese in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix eggs, milk and Bisquick together and pour over top.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: swedish cardamom meatballs
directions: In large mixing bowl, soak bread crumbs in milk for 5 minutes. Add meat, eggs, salt, pepper, cardamom and chopped onions.
Mix well and roll into 1 to 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Saute meatballs in 1/4 cup butter approximately 20 minutes.
In a separate skillet, saute sliced onions with 1/4 cup butter, sugar and pepper until caramelized, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove mixture from both pans and place on separate plates.
Deglaze both saute pans with the remaining 1/2 cup butter and beef broth, scraping up the browned bits.
Cook over high heat for 1 minute.
Place the contents of both saute pans into 1 large pot and add cream, onions, gravy maker seasoning and spices and bring to a simmer.
Make a slurry with cornstarch and water.
Whisk the slurry into the mixture to thicken.
Add meatballs and simmer approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: Fill each jar with cucumbers, 1 head dill and 2 garlic cloves.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Layer in casserole:
tortillas, chicken bits, chilies, soup and cheese.
Repeat above until casserole is full.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°, until cheese is melted.

title: jamie's chocolate chip pie
directions: Put ingredients in a pie shell in order.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over top and bake 30 to 45 minutes or until chips melt.
Very rich!
Cut in small slices.
For your conscience, all calories and fat have been removed! Enjoy!!

title: ginger raisin crinkle tops
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg until smooth. Add molasses and blend. Mix together remaining dry ingredients and combine with wet mixture. Form into walnut-sized balls and roll them in granulated sugar before placing them on an ungreased cookie sheet. Allow room for the cookie to spread. Bake for 8-10 minutes at 350 degrees, being careful not to overbake. (I do them for 10 minutes; they will not be chewy if overbaked.)

title: punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Float orange slices on top. Makes 40 (1-cup) servings.

title: johanna's tasty pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Drain off fat.
In bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Pour over pork chops.
In electric frypan, cover and simmer.
Just simmer 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
(May have to add bit of water while simmering.)

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and baking powder.
Then stir in crumbs, coconut and pecans.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until done.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix in large pan the evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat until boiling.
When it boils hard, cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows have melted.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pan.
Butterscotch chips may be used, also.

title: spiced tea
directions: Steep tea bags and spices in hot water for as long as you would in making tea.
Add all other ingredients and serve hot or over ice.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Mix well. Grease loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until well done.

title: crunchy oatmeal crust
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Press into 9-inch pie plate. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: grandma lynda's zucchini casserole
directions: Peel and slice zucchini in casserole dish.
Add chopped onion. Add all ingredients.
Stir in cheese and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add soda and salt.
Sift together three times.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add cocoa and blend.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Turn into two 9-inch pans that are greased and lined with paper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done. Cool.
Use 7 minute frosting.

title: fantastic make-ahead butterhorns
directions: In your largest mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add 4 cups of flour, milk, shortening, sugar, eggs and salt; beat for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Add enough flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto floured board; knead lightly about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise 2 to 3 hours or until doubled.
Punch dough down; divide into 4 equal parts.
Roll each into a 9-inch circle.
Cut each circle like crescent rolls.
You can then freeze on baking sheet.
When frozen, put in plastic bag.
When ready to use, thaw for 5 hours until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Butter tops.

title: down home chicken chowder
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Brown mushrooms and onions with thyme in drippings until tender.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Heat on low until hot.

title: taco tartlets
directions: To make meat shells, combine ground beef, taco seasoning and ice water. Mix well. Press meat mixture into bottom and sides of tiny tart pans and set aside.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Take 1/4 of the graham cracker mixture and cover bottom of 8 x 14-inch pan. Mix Dream Whip, sugar, milk and cream cheese until it gets a little thick.
Put on top of the graham cracker crumbs, then put the other 1/2 crumbs on top of it.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: palomino hot crab and artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine mayonnaise, artichoke hearts, crab meat, cheese and onions in an oven-safe crock.
Bake until top is golden brown; about 20 - 25 minutes.
Serve with bread or crackers.
Makes about 8 half-cup servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Add to this the tomato soup, the peas, noodles and water.
Mix and put into casserole. Sprinkle grated cheese on top and cook about 30 minutes at 350°. A little catsup can be added to the mixture.
Rice or macaroni can be substituted for the noodles.

title: mexican rice
directions: Heat shortening in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and rice and cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until done.

title: swiss potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients and stir into potatoes.
Place in baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: aaron's banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add melted oleo.
Mix in buttermilk, flour, soda and nuts.
Turn batter into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with cheese.
Saute onion in butter. Add mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Pour mixture over chicken and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: grandma estill's cake doughnuts
directions: Sift together dry ingredients except 1/2 cup flour and sugar. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Add remaining flour to mixture to make a sticky dough.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter.
Cook in deep fat fryer at 400°.
Turn often.

title: honey-baked chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine all ingredients, except rice.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, baste every 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: noodle bake
directions: Brown frankfurters with onions.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Heat oil and butter until very light, golden color.
Add garlic cloves.
Cook until slightly brown and remove.
Chicken breasts should resemble veal cutlets.
Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture, then into crumbs.
Gently brown in oil mixture for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper.
Place chicken in baking dish. Pour combined lemon juice and wine over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fish creole
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry.
Arrange in 3 quart baking dish with thick portions toward outside of dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a 4 cup measuring glass.
Pour evenly over fish. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in stick of margarine.
Mix all ingredients, except the Cheddar cheese, and place into a greased casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts good.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: supper on the porch salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve over lettuce leaf.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in 400° oven until done.

title: pikes peak potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes, place in 9 by 9 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix whip cream with chicken broth, pour over potatoes.
Bake covered for 30 minutes; then uncover and bake 30 more minutes, adding cheese the last ten minutes.
Bake until golden brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: guamanian fried rice
directions: In a large frypan, saute onion and garlic in butter.
(My wife prefers nonfat cooking spray, which she uses if she's preparing this recipe.)
Add mushrooms and frozen vegetables.
I use the Oriental style.
Sprinkle Mrs. Dash over vegetables.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Mix with sugar and marshmallows.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, stir in pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Dream Whip.
This can be made ahead of time and frozen.
Take out of freeze a while before serving.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Mix in a bowl the cream cheese.
Add the sugar.
Add one egg at a time. Add the flour, vanilla and milk. Beat until well mixed. Add pineapple slowly.
Mix with spoon.
When all mixed together, pour into 2-quart greased with butter glass dish (Pyrex). Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Shut off oven.
Let sit in oven for 1 hour, then remove to cool. Do not bake longer then 55 minutes; it may get brown around edges.

title: cool summer pie
directions: Mix
milk, pecans, coconut and pineapple.
Fold in half of whipped
topping
and pour into prepared shell.
Cover pie with remaining
topping	and
sprinkle
reserved nuts on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: salami from scratch
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate until next day.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make favorite pastry.
Core and peel apples whole.
In hole where core was, fill with butter, raisins and brown sugar.
Wrap in pastry that you have cut into squares.
Brush with egg whites, cut leaves out of pastry, using extra pastry put on apple dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Pour Catalina dressing over chicken breasts. Bake for 1 hour at 350°, then 5 minutes before chicken is taken out of oven, melt cheese on chicken.

title: creole beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain beans.
Add pork and cover with water. Cover and cook 45 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients except sausage and rice.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage; cook, uncovered, over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Yields about 12 servings.
We like this dish with Mexican Corn Bread.

title: layered salad
directions: In a deep crystal bowl layer all the ingredient in order listed.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: onion oysterettes
directions: Blend all but oysterettes in large bowl.
Pour in oysterettes. Toss gently and continue to toss every half hour until dressing is absorbed.

title: peanut butter no bakes
directions: Mix peanut butter, oleo, milk and sugar in a saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until boiling.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Take off; add 1/4 cup peanut butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Now mix in rolled oats. Drop on wax paper.

title: bourbon brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan over low heat, stirring.
Cool.
Beat in vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour and salt, and stir into chocolate mixture.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake about 25 minutes; cool.
When thoroughly cooled, crumble brownies into bowl.
Sprinkle with bourbon; mix with fingers.
Shape in 1-inch balls or logs about 1-inch long.
Roll in sugar.
Store in airtight container for a day before serving or giving as gifts.

title: shrimp and salmon rolls(serves 6)
directions: In a bowl, blend egg yolk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add oil, drop by drop, beating thoroughly between each addition.
As mayonnaise thickens, increase the flow of oil to a slow steady stream, beating constantly.
Beat in lemon juice and check seasoning.
Stir in watercress, celery and shrimp.
Layer smoked salmon slices on a work surface.
Spoon equal amounts of filling onto each slice.
Roll up salmon carefully, enclosing the shrimp filling.
Arrange 2 salmon rolls on each plate and garnish with chicory and orange slices.
Serve with brown bread and butter, as a starter or light lunch.

title: baked salmon with shrimp mirepoix
directions: Rinse salmon in cold water; pat dry.
In lightly oiled 10 x 6-inch baking dish, place salmon, skin side down.
In small saucepan over low heat in hot butter, cook vegetables until tender.
Spread vegetable mixture evenly on fish; top with shrimp and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until salmon flakes easily with a fork.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of broccoli in baking dish.
Top with 1/2 chicken. Sprinkle 1/2 of both cheeses.
Combine chicken soup, mushroom soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour half over the chicken and cheese layer.
Do the next layer the same.
Top with Velveeta.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and let the juice come to a boil.
Add eggs, flour and white sugar, which has been blended together thoroughly. Cook until smooth.

title: candie's famous chipolte spread
directions: Pour sauce over cream cheese.
Serve with triscuits.

title: kneaded chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Add sugar, milk, honey and salt.
Bring to a boil; cover and boil 2 minutes.
Uncover and cook, without stirring, until a small amount of the mixture dropped in cold water forms a soft ball (238° on a candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; add vinegar.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Then add vanilla and beat until thick and mixture loses its gloss.
Add nuts and turn out on buttered plate.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.
Knead with fingers for 4 to 5 minutes.
Shape into two rolls, each about 2-inches in diameter. Wrap in wax paper and slice when cool.

title: baking powder biscuits(granny andress cookbook)
directions: Combine and sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening (well). Add milk.
Mix with fork until dry ingredients are moist.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead gently 6 to 8 times.
Roll dough 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick for fluff biscuits.
Cut with floured 2-inch round cutter.
Arrange on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 450° until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello, sugar and cornstarch. Add water.
Cook on medium-high until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add cleaned berries to glaze.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip. This is also good with fresh peaches and peach jello.

title: best ever peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, milk and water.
Boil until mixture forms soft ball.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, but do not stir.
Cool until bottom of pan is barely warm (this is important).

title: herbed green beans with sunflower seeds
directions: Wash beans.
Drain. Cut off ends. Cook, tightly covered, in 2 cups boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes until tender-crisp.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Put rhubarb, marshmallows and sugar in shallow baking pan. Mix remaining ingredients and spread over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: orange syrup
directions: Combine
all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Stir until sugar dissolves.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In small bowl, blend pudding, Dream Whip, milk and vanilla on low speed of electric mixer.
Increase speed to higher setting (desserts) and beat until very thick.
Pour 1/3 of mixture into crust.
Layer banana slices on top of pudding, saving 1/2 banana for garnish.
Pour remaining filling into crust.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Garnish with banana slices and additional whipped topping if desired.

title: pinto beans(frijoles)
directions: Clean raw beans (make sure there are no rocks with them). Rinse thoroughly with cool water several times.
Drain and place beans in stainless 2-quart pan; add 1 quart cold water and bacon drippings or shortening.
Cook, covered, over low to medium heat 2 to 3 hours; add water as necessary to keep beans from drying, during last hour of cooking, add salt.
Makes 1 to 1 1/2 quarts beans.

title: pineapple-garlic pork chops
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sherry, brown sugar, rosemary and garlic. Place chops and marinate in plastic bag or shallow dish. Close bag securely or cover dish and marinate in refrigerator overnight, turning pork occasionally. Remove chops from marinade; reserve marinade. Place chops on rack in broiling pan so surface of meat is 4 to 5-inches from heat. Broil 11 to 13 minutes, turning and basting once with marinade. Makes 4 servings. Preparation time: 10 minutes. Marinating time: Overnight. Cooking time: 11 to 13 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese spread or cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Use as spread with vegetables, crackers or bread.

title: pie cuts
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in lukewarm milk; set aside.
Add flour and butter; cut in just like for pie crust.
Add milk and yeast to egg yolks; mix well.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll one part to fit into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling over dough and cover with remaining dough.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: nutty-buddy pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with Hershey syrup and chopped peanuts.
Freeze.

title: continental lemon sauce
directions: In small saucepan with a wire whisk, beat all ingredients until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium-low heat until thick (do not boil).
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4's.
Roll cut biscuits in mixture of sugar and 2 tablespoons of
cinnamon.
Grease a Bundt pan and arrange biscuit pieces
in layers.
Melt butter, brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Unmold immediately.
Serves 12.

title: chili con queso
directions: Place in heavy saucepan over very low heat.
Cook slowly until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm with corn chips or tortilla chips.
Also it is a great accompaniment to potatoes, rice or beans.

title: german tomato salad
directions: Chop onions fine, and tomatoes in a bowl then crumble Feta Cheese.
Prepare 2 dry package mixes using only liquid amount for one package.
Put in refrigerator for an hour before serving.

title: ms. jessie's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 pan. Then sift granulated brown sugar over the melted butter until covered well. Place pineapple in pan on top of sugar and butter. Take cherries and place 1 in the center of each slice of pineapple. Then mix cake mix, eggs, pudding and pineapple juice in a bowl and pour batter over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: quick chocolate pie shell(yields 1 pie shell; pan size:  9-inch)
directions: Place butter in glass pie plate.
Microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds or until butter is melted.
Stir in cookie crumbs. Press over bottom and side of glass plate.
Microwave on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until firm, turning dish once.
Cool.

title: easy cream of tomato soup
directions: Make white sauce of margarine, flour, salt, milk, chicken seasoning, onion and celery salt.
Heat tomatoes to boiling; add white sauce slowly to tomatoes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Cook hamburger until brown.
Remove and drain.
Cook celery and onion in hamburger drippings until tender.
Add all canned goods.
Add 3 bay leaves and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil.
Let stand, covered, for about 1 hour.
Great soup.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press into bottom of oblong (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add honey, spices and salt and blend well. Mix fruits and nuts with 1 cup flour.
Add remaining flour alternately with milk to batter.
Add fruits and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 325° for about 50 minutes.
When it tests done, cool on a cooling rack.
Slices best after cooling for a few hours.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Beat eggs, oil, salt and pepper.
Stir in Bisquick, onion, zucchini and cheese.
Fry in hot skillet like pancakes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in butter.
Stir in 3/4 cup buttermilk; make soft dough.
Knead dough 10 times on floured surface.
Roll 1/2 inch thick and cut dough with biscuit cutter. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: estelle's fruit balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar and form in balls.
If the balls don't hold together, mix a little powdered sugar in.
Roll in sugar.
Refrigerate.
These improve with age.

title: easy romaine salad
directions: Tear or chop lettuce.
Thinly slice onions.
Toss onions and lettuce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Good with or without dressing. Serve with Italian meals.

title: philly chocolate sauce
directions: Heat cream cheese, milk and chocolate over low heat; stir until sauce is smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Serve over ice cream, cake or fruit.
Yields 2 cups.
This sauce can be reheated.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Combine crab meat, shrimp, cheese, celery and scallions. Divide equally between pie crusts.
Combine mayonnaise, flour, wine and eggs.
Pour equally over mixture in pie shells.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until set.
Serve with green salad tossed with artichoke hearts.
Freezes well.
Makes 2 pies.
Each pie serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into marble size balls. Bake in 400° oven until brown, approximately 10 minutes.

title: chicken in garlic sauce
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips.
Fry in oleo.
Don't brown. In another pan, saute 3 cloves garlic and oleo.
Put fried chicken strips in a baking pan.
Pour the sauteed oil and garlic over chicken.
Add 1 can chicken broth and wine over the strips.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover for last 5 minutes of baking. Bake at 350°.

title: biscuit topped stew
directions: Stir together biscuit mix and cheese.
Add milk and stir until well blended. On floured surface, roll dough to a 5-inch circle. Cut into 6 wedges.
Set aside.

title: lemon curd
directions: Wipe lemons and grate the rinds.
Melt butter in a double boiler; add sugar, lemon juice and grated rinds.
Dissolve.
Add the beaten eggs and stir often until it thickens.
Pour into jars and cool.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: 100 cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix all other ingredients and add dry ingredients to other mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Do not overbake.

title: cheese danish
directions: Save egg white.
Put 1 package of rolls on bottom and press down.
Pour mixture onto this.
Put second package of rolls on top.
Brush with egg white and water that has been beaten up. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When taken out of oven, sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done. Let cool to touch.
Cut a 1-inch lengthwise strip from the top of each potato; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving potato shell intact.
Combine potato pulp and other ingredients except bacon in a medium to large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy; stuff potatoes with mixture. Garnish with bacon and extra cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through and cheese melted.
You can easily substitute plain yogurt for sour cream; use low-fat cheese to reduce fat content.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, add Karo, sugar, slightly beaten eggs, melted butter, vanilla and chopped pecans. Pour into (2) 9-inch uncooked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie filling is set.

title: catfish patties
directions: Boil the catfish until tender.
Pick out all bones (it comes off bones easily).
Season with salt, pepper and red pepper or hot sauce.
Add the egg and flour.
Mix well and shape into patties. Drop in small amount of oil until brown. Serve while hot.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine beans, corn, soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine margarine, crumbs and almonds; sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll between wax paper.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: sausage bean soup
directions: Saute chopped onion until brown. Add smoked sausage and let brown. Pour broth and beans. Stir. Add salt, pepper and a little thyme. Stir. Let this come to slight boil then reduce heat and simmer for about 20 min. to let all flavors mix.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Place desired amount of beef roast, potato, carrot and onion chunks in crock-pot.
Mix soups and pour over roast and vegetables.
Cook overnight or all day, or place all ingredients in tightly covered roasting pan in 350° oven for 3 hours.
Do not open oven until baking time is completed.

title: nellie's fruitcake
directions: Stir all dry
ingredients
over fruit and nuts in large bowl. Mix pure
orange
juice and well beaten eggs over fruit and dry ingredients.
Blend
thoroughly.
Line
loaf pans with brown paper (make 2
small loaves or one large loaf).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Reduce
heat
to 300° and bake approximately 1 hour. When cake is cold, wrap in cheesecloth or some type of soft cloth that has been saturated in fruit brandy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Place in large bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off grease.
Add salt, pepper and onion to your own taste.
Put in bottom of casserole dish (ungreased).
Put 1 can soup over hamburger.
Slightly brown Tater Tots in skillet (if you brown them in skillet, you won't need to cook casserole so long in oven).
Put Tater Tots on top of hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly and Tater Tots are browned and done.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Add eggs, bananas, oats and nuts.
Beat thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: salmon appetizers
directions: Drain salmon.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, salsa, parsley and cilantro.
Add cumin.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of salmon mixture over each tortilla.
Roll each tortilla up tightly and wrap individually with plastic wrap.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Slice each tortilla into bite-size pieces.
Makes about 48 appetizers.

title: pork and beans
directions: Drain juice off baked beans, then add remaining ingredients. Make sure bacon is fried before mixing.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes approximately 20 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: turkey and rice
directions: Brown turkey and green onions in a large skillet.
Add a large can of tomatoes, all spices and picante.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cooked rice and serve.

title: mia's nacho dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, chili and cheese in shallow glass or plastic dish or pie plate; microwave until warm and cheese is melted.

title: beer bread(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a sprayed (low-fat spray) bread pan.
Let rise about 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: lola faye cake
directions: Mix vegetable shortening, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix baking powder with flour and add alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to instructions on envelope.
Add cream cheese; beat on high for 2 minutes or until mixture is smooth.
Pour into 8-inch graham cracker pie shell.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill for 3 hours.
Serves approximately 6.

title: chicken breasts in raspberry sauce
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a heavy 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat; quickly roll the chicken in the margarine.
Lay the buttered paper over them; cover casserole and place in 400° oven.
After 6 minutes, press top of chicken with finger; if still soft, return to oven for a moment or two.
When the meat is springy to the touch, it is done.
Remove chicken to a warm platter and cover while making sauce.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in all ingredients.
Serve as a dip with fresh fruit.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix the margarine, sugar and milk together; boil 1 minute. Take off heat and stir in chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth and pour over cake.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake into small pieces and place in punch bowl.
Mix sour cream, milk, whipped topping and sugar until smooth.
Fold into cake.
Mix glaze and strawberries.
Pour over cake.
Chill and serve.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: spiced peanuts
directions: Boil sugar, water and spices to *hard-crack stage (300° to 310°). Drop peanuts into syrup. Stir until nuts are dry looking. Pour out on foil and let stand until cool and dry.

title: pocketbook rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in warm milk.
Add 1 cup plain flour, margarine (melted) and salt.
Beat by hand until fairly smooth. Add enough of remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Brush top of dough with butter.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down. Shape and roll fairly thin.
Cut with large biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter.
Fold in half and brush again.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
(These freeze well.)

title: pork chops and spanish rice
directions: For spicier flavor, add 1/4 teaspoon Tabasco sauce.

title: velvet custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set out pie shell.
In a small saucepan, scald milk over high heat; set aside.

title: quick coq au vin
directions: Combine flour, thyme and salt in a zip-top bag; add chicken. Seal and shake to coat. Remove chicken from bag and shake off excess flour mixture. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook 8 minutes or until browned, turning frequently. Remove chicken from pan. Add mushrooms, carrots and bacon to pan; saut 2 minutes. Stir in wine, broth and tomato paste; cook 9 minutes. Return chicken to pan; cook 8 minutes or until chicken is done. Yield: 6 servings (serving size about 1 1/4 cups).

title: fluffy yogurt jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to the package.
Chill until Jell-O begins to set, whip with electric mixer.
Fold in yogurt and chill.
Serve when Jell-O is firm.

title: samuel's lasagna
directions: Brown the beef with chopped onion in skillet.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package and drain.
When beef is cooked, drain well and add spaghetti sauce; mix well.

title: sweet potato souffl
directions: Cook and mash potatoes. Stir in sugar, egg yolks, butter, salt and vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold into potato mixture. Pour into 9 x 12 casserole. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Serves 8. Can do ahead.

title: most eggcellent egg custard pie
directions: Mix together eggs (except 2 whites), sugar, flour, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 egg whites and add to mixture.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until straw comes out clean, usually about an hour.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat, onion and green pepper in large skillet until done. Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes or until thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: pork chop and potato dinner
directions: Put potatoes into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper over potatoes.
Season and trim fat from pork chops.
Cook fat until crisp.
Remove from skillet. Brown pork chops slowly on both sides in fat in skillet, then put on top of potatoes in baking dish.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat.
Brown meatballs and add to liquid mixture.
Simmer 1 hour on low.

title: granny's banana bread
directions: Beat mashed bananas for a few minutes to make they soupy. Cream shortening and sugar together; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and beat until flour disappears.
Add bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender (do not overcook).
Chop after draining.
Mix onion, soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
In casserole dish, put 1/2 of rice with 1/2 of soup/cheese mixture over it. Spread broccoli and rest of rice.
Pour rest of soup/cheese mixture over rice and top with buttered bread crumbs (or crushed crackers).
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: bit o' brickle squares
directions: Mix cake mix and butter with mixer until crumbly.
Press mixture into an oblong pan.
Then mix eggs, pecans, Bit O' Brickle bits, milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour over cake mixture. Spread evenly.
Bake at 325 degrees until browned around edges and slightly on top.
Center will be loose but will setup when cooled. Slice into squares.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick and foamy.
Stir in pineapple and zucchini. Combine remaining ingredients, stirring gently (just enough to blend).
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (test center with toothpick).
Cool on racks.
Freezes very well.

title: no potatoes potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; makes enough for a large crowd.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: all vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and put into a casserole dish. Top with a mixture of crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle onion, salt and pepper over potatoes and pour half the oleo over this mixture.
Heat soup, sour cream and Cheez Whiz.
Then pour over the potatoes. Top with with corn flakes or Rice Krispies and the other half of the oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: In buttered casserole, put the cream cheese and sour cream. Add the minced onion, cooked chopped meat, tomato sauce and ketchup, salt and pepper to taste and garlic powder.
With cooked noodles, combine everything together and top with the slices of cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Combine flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Beat egg with milk in a separate bowl then stir in apple and butter.
Add all at once to flour mixture and stir until just moistened (batter will be very stiff).

title: graham break-aways
directions: Arrange crackers on cookie sheet (size to fit crackers). Combine in large bowl the butter and brown sugar; microwave 3 1/2 to 4 minutes on High, stirring halfway 3 times.
Stir until smooth.
Spread over crackers.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes until browned and bubbly.

title: lemon chicken with bulgur
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In a 4-quart pan, heat oil, then brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken from pan and set aside.
In the pan, brown the onion and garlic.
Add more oil, if needed.
Add the bulgur.
Stir mixture to coat.
Add cardamom, coriander, cumin, lemon rind and lemon juice to the bulgur and onion mixture.
Mix well.
Remove mixture from pan.
Arrange chicken in bottom of pan.
Spoon bulgur mixture on top of chicken. Pour boiling chicken broth over the chicken and bulgur.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Heat tomatoes in a large pan.
Let simmer.
Add chili block, chili powder and Tabasco.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Add hamburger and onion.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes more.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar with 1 1/2 quarts water.
Add pineapple juice and then ginger ale or Sprite.
Stir to blend well.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread in bottom of 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice
directions: Mix in crock-pot the 3 cans of soup and rice (uncooked). Place chicken on top of mixture, then add the celery.
(Hint:
I sprinkle with Morton Nature's Seasons to taste.) Cook in crock-pot for 3 hours on high or for 4 hours on low.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits, water and salt for 5 minutes.
Add margarine and cheese.
Remove from heat and stir until dissolved.
Beat 2 eggs slightly in a cup and then fill with milk.
Add to grit mixture and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
A dash of cayenne pepper or paprika may be added.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough onto a pizza pan and cook to package instructions.
Let cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheddar grits and sausage bake
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until no longer pink; drain well. Meanwhile, in a large saucepan, bring water to boiling.
Slowly add grits, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until boiling again.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 5 minutes or until water is absorbed and mixture is thick, stirring occasionally. Add 1 cup of the cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Remove pan from the heat.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut sirloin into 1/8 inch strips.
Mix soy sauce, ginger and garlic.
Marinate beef in sauce in refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours. Brown meat and sauce in large skillet.
Reduce heat to low and add onion and tomatoes.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Turn heat to medium and add cornstarch and water.
Remove
from heat when gravy thickens. Serve over white rice.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: corn fritters southern style
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, milk and salad oil.
Stir in flour mixture, then corn.
Drop by tablespoon into fat heated to 365° in deep fat fryer or fry in hot pan and turn once.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well after each egg.
Add buttermilk.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt, then add to sugar mixture.
Blend well.
Add vanilla, mashed bananas and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.

title: tempting macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, raisins, celery, bell pepper and apples; blend mayonnaise with ginger, curry, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix with pasta; chill.
Arrange and sprinkle with peanuts.

title: banana split
directions: Mix margarine and graham cracker crumbs and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, butter and powdered sugar (no less than 15 minutes).
Spread over crust.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Cover bananas with No. 2 can crushed pineapple, well drained.
Cover all this with 1 box Cool Whip, then sprinkle 3/4 cup chopped nuts and top with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: the best pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans until well blended. Add pecans last.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake approximately 55 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into a loaf about 9 x 5 x 3-inches and put in a loaf dish. Spread Heinz ketchup over top, if desired.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on Medium-high for 22 to 24 minutes or until no longer pink.
Do not overcook.
Allow to stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: nick's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Use on any meat.

title: doggie biscuits
directions: Turn oven to 300°.
Mix the first 7 ingredients with a wooden spoon in a large bowl.
Dissolve yeast thoroughly in warm water (110° to 115°) in glass measuring cup.
Add to dry ingredients. Add chicken broth to flour mixture.
Stir until dough forms.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Sort, wash and drain dry beans.
Prepare beans by overnight or quick-soak method.
Cook, using soaking liquid, adding more water if needed, until beans are tender (1 1/2 hours).
Drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Drain canned vegetables and add all the beans and green pepper to the mixture. Mix well.
Cover and chill 6 hours or longer.
Mix well before serving.

title: lickety-split cocoa cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; stir with spoon or wire whisk just until batter is smooth and ingredients are well blended.

title: cranberry-pineapple relish
directions: Gently boil first 3 ingredients together until all berries have popped.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Add pineapple.
Mix and chill.
Chopped walnuts may be added.

title: great-aunt ruth's favorite gingersnaps
directions: Sift into a bowl the flour, baking soda and ginger.
Place to one side.
In another bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Then blend in egg, molasses, vinegar and cold water.
Now add sifted dry ingredients.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Saute butter, green pepper and garlic powder and remove green pepper, then add flour, milk, salt, pepper, basil, oregano and sugar.
Cook and stir until thickens, then add tomatoes, corn and onions.
Mix all ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hamburger and rice stuffing
directions: Brown hamburger.
Rinse under warm water to get oil off.
Mix all ingredients together.
Two choices, you can stuff or you can bake.
If you bake, bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.
(Quick tip:
You can use instant rice but only use one can of broth.
Combine the broth when cooking instant rice.)
Do not put cover on this dish when in oven.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt together; add coloring, then add 4 1/2 cup corn flakes. Do not crush up.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Put red hot cinnamon candy on top for holly berries.

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Heat sugar, corn syrup and water in a 3-quart saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, blend in butter.
Stir frequently.
When temperature reaches 280°, add peanuts.
Stir constantly until temperature reaches 305°, hard crack stage.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef and put cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes and cooked ground beef in crock-pot.
Cook on medium heat until all cheese is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with apples, pears, etc. Dip fruit in Sprite to keep from turning brown.

title: shrimp or crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute on medium heat butter, onions and bell peppers about 1/2 hour.
Add Ro-Tel and cook for another 15 minutes.
Add soups and heat until slow boil.
Add shrimp or crawfish and continue to cook for another 30 minutes.
If this mixture is too thin, add a small amount of cornstarch and water.
Add salt, black pepper, Season-All, garlic powder, parsley and Tabasco to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Heat sugar, butter, honey and molasses until sugar dissolves. Stir in eggs, almonds and citron.
Sift together flour and spices. Stir into mixture.
Chill dough.

title: my taco dip
directions: Brown chuck well; add taco seasonings and tomatoes.
Stir well.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes until heated.
Top with cheese. Serve with nacho chips.

title: celebrity fudge
directions: Break sweet chocolate into squares.
Place in large bowl with chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Bring sugar, salt, butter and milk to boil, stirring occasionally, for 6 minutes.

title: meat loaf (a meal in one)
directions: Mix ground beef, catsup, eggs, crackers, bread, salt and pepper together.
Beat and punch down mixture well (the more you beat and punch down mixture, the more firm your meat loaf will be).
Shape into oblong shape or ball and put in deep baking pan or dish.
Put sliced potatoes, carrots and onion around meat loaf. Add water.
Cover and bake at 375° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and carrots are soft and done.
(Make sure the water does not cook all the way out, you might have to add a little more.
This makes the meat loaf moist.)

title: oven-barbecued frankfurters
directions: Pierce each frankfurter several times with a fork, and place in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine flour and water in a small bowl, stirring until smooth.
Add next 9 ingredients, stirring well; pour over frankfurters.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve in warm buns.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: ma's armenian raised rolls
directions: Whenever we celebrated a holiday or our family had a special dinner, my Mom would always bring her special homemade rolls. Every time I make these, I always think of her.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 8-inch shallow baking dish. Arrange potatoes, slightly overlapping in single layer in dish. Mix cheese, bread crumbs, rosemary and pepper.
In small bowl, stir milk and gravy mix until well blended.
Pour evenly over potatoes.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and topping is golden.
Garnish with rosemary sprigs.

title: chili
directions: Heat
olive oil; add ground meat.
Sear over high heat, stirring
constantly,
until meat is gray.	Add water and cook covered at a bubbly simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add all remaining ingredients,
except
flour and meal.
Cook another 30 minutes at same
bubbly simmer.
Next add thickening mixed with 1 cup cold water.
Cook 5 minutes longer to determine if more water is needed for desired consistency.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine eggs, mayonnaise and soup; mix with remaining ingredients.
Top with Ritz crackers. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake next day for one hour at 350°.

title: praline candy
directions: Stir together sugar, salt, soda, corn syrup and buttermilk. Cook over low heat without stirring to 236°, or soft ball stage. Move from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Let cool to 120° and beat until creamy.
Stir in nuts and quickly drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: "mama's" egg custard
directions: Beat 3 egg yolks plus 1 whole egg and margarine together.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add sugar mixture along with milk and vanilla alternately to egg mixture, beating well.
Pour into unbaked deep pie shell.
Bake about 1 hour at 300°.
Shake about every 15 minutes.
Take out of oven when center is about the size of a quarter that still shakes.
Set out while you beat the 3 egg whites, sweetened with 5 tablespoons sugar.
Spoon atop custard. Return to oven until whites are slightly brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: In bowl, combine pineapple and juice and pudding mix; blend well.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve in individual dishes.

title: taco dip
directions: Add
taco seasoning to softened cream cheese and mix well.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Flake the chicken over water and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and cook until tender.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Place spaghetti in 2 quarts boiling water until tender. Brown ground beef, onions and peppers in skillet while spaghetti cooks. Drain spaghetti. Add ground beef, water and spaghetti sauce. Stir. Pour into 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue chuck roast
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate roast 2 to 3 hours.
Bake approximate time for size of roast.
Leave marinade in the roasting pan and baste as needed.
Slice and serve with marinade on the side.
May use sifted cornstarch to thicken to desired consistency.
Plan 4 ounces meat per person.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix all together.
Store in refrigerator in plastic bag.
Will keep 4 or 5 weeks.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake a 9-inch deep dish pie shell at 400° for 5 minutes. Peel, slice and drain tomatoes on paper towels.
Put tomatoes in shell.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil and onions.

title: chicken salad mold
directions: In large bowl, soften gelatin in cold water for 10 minutes. Add all other ingredients except whipped cream; mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Place in oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and refrigerate until firm.
Unmold and slice thin to serve.
Place on watercress or lettuce leaves.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine flour and mayonnaise with fork until well blended. Add milk and mix.
Fill greased muffin pan 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May chill.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: butter rice
directions: Mix salt and 2 cups water, bring to a boil and pour over rice. Let stand 30 minutes.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice and cook over medium heat, stirring 5 minutes.
Put in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic salt. Pour broth over rice.
Cover, bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Uncover, bake 10 minutes more after adding parsley.

title: jello surprise
directions: Boil 2 cups of water.
Pour into gelatin.
Stir for 2 minutes until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Let chill until firm. In bowl mix Cool Whip, bananas and crushed pineapple.

title: scalloped potatoes and mushrooms
directions: Mix in 2-quart dish, then pour mixture of soup and milk over potatoes.
Cover with lid or tin foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all juices together and pour over 2 trays of ice in punch bowl.
Add	ginger	ale
and
serve.
This	may also be "spiked".

title: potato soup
directions: In a saucepan, boil potatoes, carrots, onions and dill in water until tender.
Pour most of water out and add milk.

title: potato casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer potatoes, then cheese, onions and bread cubes.
Drizzle margarine over top.
Sprinkle rest of ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, butter flavor Crisco, eggs, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Roll balls of dough in mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 or 8 minutes.

title: crab squares
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Lightly toast one side.
Cut each toasted slice into 4 squares.
Set aside.
Drain and flake canned or thaw, drain and flake frozen crabmeat in medium bowl.
Combine crabmeat, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and Worcestershire sauce in a second medium bowl.
Beat egg white until stiff but not dry. Fold into crabmeat mixture.
Spoon about 2 teaspoons on untoasted side of each toast square.
Preheat oven.
Place oven shelf 5 or 8 inches from heating element.
Place squares in broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes until browned and bubbly.
Makes 24 servings.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar until thickened.
Cool to room temperature; do not chill.
Mix with cream cheese and pecans while still slightly warm.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Beat all together until creamy if too thick.
Add a little milk.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into an ungreased baking dish.
Spread to corner of dish.
Add pineapple and spread evenly over the cherries.
Spread cake mix over this.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over the dry cake mix.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let set for 2 hours before serving.

title: no salt seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small jar with a shaker top and use in place of salt.

title: indian corn meal
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9-inch loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned. Can be wrapped and frozen for later use.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook ground turkey.
Drain.
Add spinach, tomatoes (undrained), spices and cottage cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and beat.
Beat eggs in margarine and sugar.
Mash crackers; put into pan, then layer bananas, crushed pineapple, then start over until you run out of pineapple. Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: With wooden spoon, beat vigorously 30 seconds after soft dough forms. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vermont tea
directions: Mix syrup with tea.
Add ice for iced tea.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour 3 full tablespoons of mixture into a hot Teflon or greased 6-inch skillet.
Cook until firm, then turn over and cook for 30 seconds. It should look like a thin crepe.
Makes about 18 shells.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: 4 Brown sausage in a saucepan, stirring until crumbly. Stir in flour, cook until of a roux consistency, stirring constantly. Add the milk and half and half and mix well. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring occasionally stir in the sauerkraut and lemon juice. Cook over low heat for 5 to 140 minutes or until desired consistency.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer with whole green chilies, Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese.
Repeat layers until chilies are all used.
Beat eggs, flour and milk.
Pour over layered mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over casserole and bake additional 10 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: double cheeseburger casserole(serves 6)
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Drain. Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, salt and pepper. Cook until heated through. Layer ground beef mixture and cheese slices alternately in casserole. Arrange biscuits on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: fruit tea
directions: Boil water then add tea bags. Cover and steep for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Remove tea bags. Add rest of ingredients. Stir. Fill gallon pitcher rest of way with water.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar, mustard and cornstarch.
Slowly add vinegar. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Makes 2 cups.

title: braised pork with hominy and peppers
directions: Tie garlic cloves and peppercorns in cheesecloth.
In heavy large saucepan, combine cheesecloth package, 10 cups water, pork, sliced onion and bay leaves.
Bring to simmer over medium-high heat, skimming foam from surface.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer uncovered 1 hour.
Using slotted spoon, transfer pork and onions to medium bowl.
Strain broth and reserve.
Discard contents of strainer.

title: mexican apple pie
directions: Heat together sugar, water and margarine.
Spoon apples onto tortillas.
Roll up and place seam down in an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour sugar mixture over this and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine with 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar and crumbs together.
Put in bottom of large pan (13 x 9-inch).
Mix confectioners sugar, eggs and two sticks margarine. Beat in mixer for 10 to 15 minutes until creamy and thick.
Mix in drained pineapple.
Place on top of crumb crust.
Slice 5 or 6 bananas lengthwise.
Lay on top of mixture.
Stir up Cool Whip and place over top.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: buzzy the clown
directions: Flatten out 2 cupcake liners (use 2 different colors) on your plate.
Dip opening of ice cream cone into honey, just slightly. Dip opening of ice cream cone with honey on it into coconut.
Place a scoop of vanilla ice cream on flattened out cupcake liners. Place ice cream with honey and coconut on top of scoop of ice cream.
Place raisins to form mouth and place M&M's for eyes.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour and dry yeast. Set aside.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all together, adding cornbread mix last.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with chips.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Mix cocoa and food coloring together to make a paste; add to batter.
In small bowl, combine flour and salt.
In another small bowl, add vanilla to buttermilk.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk to batter beginning and ending with flour, mixing well after each addition. Add soda to vinegar and pour into batter; mix well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: peach crumble
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch square baking pan. Arrange peaches in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over peaches.
Bake until topping is golden brown and peaches are hot, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Put into kettle the kidney beans, tomatoes, chili powder and salt to taste.
Add red pepper.
In skillet, cook hamburger, onion, garlic powder, oil, celery, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Add hamburger ingredients to kettle and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamed chicken(pollo en crema)
directions: Put salt and pepper over skinned legs and fry in a pan with oil.
In a separate pan saute onion and chiles poblanos for around 10 minutes in low fire.
Pour the cream and when chicken is golden, put in also.
Let chicken stay in mixture for 4 to 6 minutes on low fire.
Serve.

title: french toast roll ups
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the cream cheese, egg yolk, and 1/4 c. sugar until smooth; set aside.

title: turkey soup
directions: Precook noodles.
Mix vegetables, juice and turkey and cook. Add noodles last.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello	in
hot
water.
Let
stand to thicken. Line bottom of
pan
with
cracker crumbs (save some for top). Soften cream cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat cream until thick; add cheese
mixture
and
whipped cream to jello, which has thickened somewhat.
Beat
until
fluffy.
Pour into pan. Top with remaining crumbs and cool.
Very good.

title: baked fish
directions: Using fish fillets, either leave in large pieces or cut into serving sizes.
Place fish in oiled pan, and sprinkle with crackers and melted butter.
Blend crackers and melted butter before sprinkling on fish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
If fish is thicker, bake slightly longer.
Most delicious!

title: chicken dijon
directions: Melt butter and cook chicken and onion on low heat 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Mix soup, milk, mustard and parsley together. Pour into pan; add chicken and onion.
Heat and serve over cooked noodles.

title: butter bean soup
directions: Prepare all veggies first.
Into 4 to 6-quart soup pot put beans and broth along with chicken broth and water.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to boiling point, reduce heat and simmer about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with tossed green salad and fresh fruit cup.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook frozen broccoli in 1 cup water according to package directions.
When done, drain well.
Lightly grease 1 to 2-quart baking dish.
While broccoli is hot, mix broccoli, soup and cheese together.
Pour into baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs and margarine with fork until moist.
Top broccoli mixture with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes.
(If any leftover, may be reheated in microwave.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and add to crushed Ritz crackers.
Place cracker mixture in greased casserole dish and add drained broccoli.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and 1/2 pound cheese in double boiler or microwave oven and pour over broccoli.
Top by sprinkling more crushed crackers over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: sunny banana pie
directions: Slice bananas into crust.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk into the cream cheese (softened), mixing until smooth and well blended. Add pudding mix and remaining milk and small amounts of flavorings.
Beat slowly for about 2 minutes.
Pour into crust over bananas.
Sprinkle toasted coconut over top and chill.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream if desired.

title: *icebox pudding
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Reserve some for topping.
Line pan with other crumbs.
Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs and flavoring; beat thoroughly.
Spread mixture over vanilla wafers in pan.
Combine crushed pineapple, nuts, mashed bananas and lemon juice.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar to the smoothly whipped cream and fold into fruit mixture.
Pour over crushed wafers. Cover top with reserved crushed wafers.
Put in the refrigerator and let set for about 8 hours before serving.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serves 8.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 crumbs in a well greased pie pan. Beat egg whites-gradually add sugar and beat until stiff and glossy. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemony. Fold into egg whites, cream. Add lemon rind & juice, mix well. Fold into egg mixture. Pour into pan. Top with crumbs. Freeze.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together thoroughly; mixture may be soft.
Form into small balls and cook in 1/4 lb. butter.
When browned well, remove from pan.
In butter remaining in pan, add 1/4 cup flour, and 1 pint sour cream.
Stir well, scraping up all browned bits at bottom of pan.
Add 1 teaspoon parsley.
Return meatballs to pan and heat thoroughly.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup water to sauce if it's too thick.

title: zapp burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make hamburger patties; grill.

title: almond glazed poppy seed bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, milk, butter and oil.
Then add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix with a mixer 2 minutes.
Add extracts and poppy seed.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and milk. Stir in pecans. Drop by spoonful on wax paper (buttered).
Put melted chocolate on top after cooling awhile.
The baking chocolate is what I use.

title: "jesse" salad (smith)
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, oil, pepper and salt for 1 minute.
Pour this mixture over the vegetables.
Mix well and allow to marinate. Next, eat and enjoy!

title: louisiana mud pie
directions: Mix butter and flour in rectangular baking dish.
Press chopped pecans in mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° and cool. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar and spread over crust.
Mix pudding according to directions on package and pour over crust. Spread the Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream and seasoned salt if desired. Mix well. Add to pea mixture; toss to coat. Chill until serving.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together the eggs, pumpkin, sugar, Milnot and pumpkin pie spice.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix, margarine and nuts over pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.
You may never bake another pumpkin pie!

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together and let set in refrigerator 1 hour at least.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Blend together sugar, eggs, flour and baking powder.
Add butter or margarine, which has been melted in 1 cup hot milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cranberry butter
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Chill.
Keeps for 2 weeks. Excellent on breads, rolls and muffins.

title: chicken corn mini pies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin tin.
Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise; stir in other ingredients.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 2 parts.
Place bottom part in muffin tins.
Press to cover bottom and sides.
Pour mixture into cup.
Top with remaining biscuit, stretching to fit.
Press sides to seal.
Sprinkle with sesame seed, if desired.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover with a layer of "soda crackers".
Combine the oleo and sugar in a saucepan and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup Colby cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
put	in a buttered casserole dish. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: walnut spread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together in a bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
May add CASHEW MAYONNAISE for smoother texture.
Spread on bread.
Garnish with alfalfa sprouts and tomato.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Roll into balls. Press with a fork to flatten. Bake 8 to 12 minutes in 350° oven. Cool on cookie sheet. Can drizzle with melted chocolate.

title: tuna pick-ups
directions: Roll patty shells into 6 x 8-inch rectangles; cut each rectangle into eighths.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of tuna mixture on each piece of dough.
Roll up.
Seal ends with fork.
Place, seam side down, on foil pan made from aluminum foil.
With grill hood closed, cook over hot coals, 20 to 30 minutes, turning to brown on all sides.
Can cook in oven at 350° until brown.
