Makes 48 appetizers.

title: cauliflower-bacon salad
directions: Mix dressing, Parmesan cheese, sugar and onion in large bowl. Add bacon, cauliflower and lettuce.
Toss.
Serve immediately.

title: russian tea
directions: Put in large jar.
Use as instant tea 2 teaspoons to one cup hot water.
Sweeten with 1 teaspoon honey.

title: owens' peanut butter candy
directions: Boi sugar and milk to soft ball stage (240° on candy thermometer).
In mixing bowl, mix Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over this the boiled mixture and mix well.
Spread in buttered cake pan.
You can melt 5 or 6 Hershey bars and spread on top.
This will be like Reese's peanut butter cups.
Very good.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges and add juice of both to cornstarch and sweetener (or sugar).
Cook until thick.
Set aside to cool while preparing apples and grapes.
When sauce is cool, mix together.
Add sliced bananas within an hour of eating time.

title: granny's biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder into a large bowl.
Mix in shortening with a spoon. Pour milk over flour, a little at a time (the dough needs to be a little stiff).
Add a little flour on a cutting board.
Knead and add flour if dough is sticking to hands.
Roll out dough on board; use a cookie cutter or drinking glass to cut out biscuits.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: homemade white bread
directions: Warm milk and butter to very warm (not hot); test on your wrist as you would a baby bottle.
In bowl, combine yeast, sugar and salt with milk and butter.
Stir gently.
Add 3 cups flour and stir until blended.
Add rest of flour.
Turn out onto floured surface. Knead 10 minutes.
Place in lightly greased bowl, turn once, for 1 1/2 hours or until double.
Turn out; divide in half.
Shape into 2 loaves and place in pans.
Let rise again 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and wrap for freshness.
Makes 2.

title: texas trash(makes 10 cups)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large shallow roasting pan, toss the cereals with the oats, pretzel sticks, crackers and nuts. In a small bowl, whisk the remaining ingredients and drizzle over the cereal mixture.
Toss quickly to mix well.
Bake for 20 minutes or until crisp and golden, stirring several times.

title: savory or sweet scones
directions: Place flour, salt and baking powder in a bowl.
Add sugar if making sweet scones.
Rub (mix) butter into dry ingredients.
Add cheese for savory or fruit for sweet.
Slowly add milk, a little at a time, and mix with a knife to start.
Use clean hands to finish mixing.
Mixture should not crumble when picked up or be too sticky.
Roll on a floured board.
Cut into approximately 12 scones 1-inch high.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden. Serve hot or cold.
Butter and serve savory scones for lunch and sweet scones for morning or afternoon tea.
May also add chopped bacon or onion for savory scones.

title: steak and onions
directions: Heat
margarine
and
oil in a 10-inch Dutch oven.
Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally until onions are limp and slightly browned.
Remove from pan.
Add coals to Dutch oven so	it is hot.
Add steak and quickly brown.
Cook at medium
heat until
done.
Remove meat.
Add broth to pan. Heat and
stir. Add
onions and heat well.	Spoon onions over meat.

title: easter bread(pascha)
directions: Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
Add butter and eggs and mix together.
Combine dry yeast with flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add flour mixture slowly to cottage cheese mix, beating well after each addition until dough is stiff.
Dust raisins with flour; add to flour mixture.
Cover bowl with a towel and let rise in a warm spot about 1 hour until doubled.
Punch down and turn into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Let rise again 40 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with soft butter. Sprinkle with a few pinches of salt.
Cool 10 minutes in pan; complete cooling on a rack.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt margarine in pan. Put sugar, graham crackers and peanut butter in large bowl. Add margarine and mix well. Melt chocolate chips in pan. Press peanut butter mixture into ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Smooth melted chips on top. Refrigerate several hours. Before cutting, let stand at room temperature about 1/2 hour.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown beef in large skillet and drain fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chilies and taco seasoning.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, blend Ricotta cheese and eggs.
In a baking dish, layer 1/2 beef mixture, then 1/2 chips.
Spread 1/2 of Ricotta cheese mixture over chips, then sprinkle with 1/2 Monterey Jack.
Continue layering.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: quick and easy banana nut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and water in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed on electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Batter should be light and fluffy.
Peel and chop bananas into cake batter.
Beat at high speed for 1 minute more.
Fold in nuts.

title: red beet sauce for baked ham
directions: Grate beets or put in blender.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend until almost smooth.
Serve in a dish as a condiment for ham.

title: country club corn
directions: Mix milk, corn, salt and
pepper.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Cut margarine into small pieces.
Arrange over corn. Crumble crackers and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° until browned. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla together, adding sugar gradually. Then add flour and baking powder.
Heat milk and butter until hot, do not boil.
Add to mixture.
Pour into two 9-inch round baking pans.
Put in oven then turn on to 375°.
Bake for 20 minutes, then check.

title: garlic and herb chicken
directions: Coat chicken lightly with flour.
Brown in skillet with 2 tablespoons oil.
Top with Hunt's chunky garlic and herb sauce. Simmer, covered, 20 to 30 minutes or until cooked through.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine with sour cream.
Add taco seasoning; mix well.
Drain salsa well.
Spread on top of sour cream mixture.
Place chopped onion on top of salsa, then place lettuce on top of that.
Next, layer the cheese, then tomatoes. Serve as is, layered, not mixed!
Serve on top of large, plain (no-frills) nacho chips.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with Pam.
In prepared dish, layer chicken breasts.
In medium bowl, combine cranberries, Catalina dressing and soup mix.
Stir until well combined.
Pour over chicken, making sure it coats completely.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and cranberries form a glaze.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Drain oranges.
Combine juice with remaining ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Cover and simmer gently for 45 minutes.
Stir in orange sections just before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.
Good with brown, wild rice.

title: creamy peas and onions
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine frozen vegetables and water.
Cook, covered on 100% power (High) in microwave for 7 to 9 minutes or until just tender.
Drain well.
Stir in the cream cheese, milk, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook, covered on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until heated thorough, stirring once.
Makes 5 servings.

title: shirley's organic biscuits
directions: Recommended ingredients are:
Arrowhead Mills Organic Flour, multi-grain, pastry flour or Spelt.
For milk use Organic Valley nonfat dry milk or goats milk or Chrome Dairy hormone and antibiotic free milk.
Use Ghee clarified butter (from Purity Farms) or goat butter.

title: black eyed pea casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a heavy skillet and drain drippings; remove sausage and set aside. In skillet, saute onion in oil until soft. Cut chicken breasts into strips and cook in skillet until browned and almost done. Combine sausage, onion and chicken strips with remaining ingredients in a 2 quart baking dish; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Uncover and cook for 15 minutes. Serve over rice or pasta.

title: chicken sunday dinner
directions: Spread rice in greased glass dish.
Layer chicken over rice. Sprinkle with pepper, salt and onion soup mix.
Top with mushroom soup and water.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: quick irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
With knife, cut shortening into biscuit mix until like coarse cornmeal.
Stir in sugar, raisins and caraway seed.
With fork, stir in milk until blended well.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate; spread smooth.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Add stew beef to crock-pot on low in a.m.
Let it cook all day. Shred beef with fingers and return to pot.
Add barbecue sauce; heat 20 minutes longer.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars.
Add eggs one at a time. Blend well. Add vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal, sliced oranges, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Lightly grease 9-inch square pan.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce over bottom of dish.
Arrange uncooked noodles in dish.
Combine Ricotta, eggs, basil, oregano and Parmesan cheese; spread over noodles.
Top with noodles and 1/2 cup sauce.
Combine zucchini, salt, pepper and flour.
Spoon into dish; top with more noodles and rest of sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle with Mozzarella and bake about 15 minutes.
Let cool about 15 minutes before cutting.

title: chocolate pudding cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk; blend until smooth.
Add remaining milk and pie filling mix; beat at lowest speed of electric mixer until blended, about 1 minute.
Pour at once into pie shell.
Chill for at least 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large boiler, put broccoli, onion, celery, seasonings and a couple of bouillon cubes.
Cook until broccoli is tender.
Add half of the butter while cooking.
Drain most of the juice, leaving a little.
Add rice and mix.
Add Cheez Whiz; stir.
Put in a baking dish and bake about 45 minutes.

title: florida vegetable salad
directions: Bring to boil the first 6 ingredients, then set aside to cool. Pour over remaining vegetables.
Drain peas and beans.
Will keep 1 to 2 weeks.

title: devilish cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Makes about 2 cups dip.

title: creole corn
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add taco season
to beef and follow directions on season packet for water.
Set aside.

title: halloween punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and sugar together in gallon container. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Pour in punch bowl; add pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Makes 55 punch cup servings.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, nutmeg, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir in pineapple and apple until blended.
Grease and lightly flour a 12 x 9 x 2-inch sheet cake pan.
Spread batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Mash.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.
Stir often.

title: old fashion apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Add apples and vanilla.
Sift flour; add soda, salt and cinnamon, adding to the other ingredients.
Add the nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool before you add the icing to the cake.

title: simpson family favorite christmas cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add hot water and soda.
Stir.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour, a little at a time.
Mix 1/2 cup flour with raisins and nuts, along with cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add to egg mixture all of flour.
Then add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake approximately 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Do not burn!!

title: easy chicken drummettes
directions: Place butter in a microwave
baking dish and microwave on full power for 30 to 45 seconds or until melted. Rinse and dry chicken pieces.
Cut wings at joints, separating each into 3 sections.
Discard tops.
Dip remaining pieces in melted butter.
Combine bread crumbs, almonds, salt, parsley, garlic powder and pepper.
Coat chicken pieces.
Place half of wings in a dish with small end toward the middle.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 24 appetizers.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to the directions on the box.
Pour cake mix into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Dice all ingredients, except shells.
Add spices, vinegar and oil.
Best if made night before use.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed shrimp(serves 2)
directions: Remove shell of shrimp up to tail.
Cut shrimp down to the back, leaving in butterfly fashion.
Remove vein.
Place in baking dish.
Melt butter; combine remaining ingredients.
Place stuffing in each shrimp.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until tails curl up and shrimp meat is bright white.
Serve with drawn butter and lemon wedge.

title: sue's potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place into a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice hotel rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine milk, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Place about 1 tablespoon rice and a few plumped raisins in the bottom of each of 8 custard cups.
Fill with custard.
Place cups in pan of water and bake about 30 minutes, until a silver knife inserted in center of custard comes out clean.
Do not overbake. Cool and turn into serving dishes.
Top with vanilla sauce.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, tomato and eggs.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and mix well.

title: lemon squares
directions: In a small bowl, cream together the margarine and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Add 2 cups of flour; stir well with wooden spoon.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan; set aside.

title: grandma's beef barbecue
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain.
Add pepper and remaining ingredients. Simmer 1/2 hour. Serve on buns.

title: dottie's favorite pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, oats, vanilla, powdered sugar and coconut in large bowl.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate for 30 minutes or until cold. Melt in small pan on low heat paraffin wax and chocolate chips. Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate mixture.
Let set a few minutes and serve.

title: yuletide scrambled eggs
directions: Add pimiento and green pepper to eggs before cooking.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Lay spareribs in baking pan.
Cover with sauce made from listed ingredients and bake 2 1/2 hours at 325° or until tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour pecans in bottom of pie shell.
Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Mix in the eggs, Karo syrup and vanilla. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Blend in lemon juice and catsup until creamy.
Slowly add juice from can of shrimp until blended thoroughly.
Add shrimp, either whole or cut up, depending on size.
Chill several hours.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in 3-quart saucepan; drain.
Add sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook lasagna according to package directions; drain (separate lasagna and lay out flat on wax paper to keep pieces from sticking together).
Combine cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper for filling.

title: stuffed calamari
directions: Slowly heat tomato sauce.
Meanwhile, in medium-size bowl, soak bread crumbs and drop of water to dampen.
Set aside.
Clean squid bodies and legs thoroughly.
Soak in cold water until ready to use. Finely chop onion and garlic; saute in olive oil.
When onions are soft, mix the mixture into bread crumbs; add parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Loosely stuff squid bodies with mixture.
Close open end with toothpick.
Raise temperature of sauce and add squid. Cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: batter-dipped chicken
directions: Cut large fryer in serving size pieces.
Wash.
Partially cook in boiling water for 20 minutes; drain.
Sprinkle with salt, celery salt and pepper.
Dip in batter.
Drop in hot fat (360°). Fry until golden brown, 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt
the
cocoa in water and oleo and bring to a boil. Remove.
While
hot, add the flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Beat in the eggs, sour cream and soda.
Pour into a greased 11 x 17	x
1-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine ingredients.
Next morning, drain well and rinse slightly.
Divide mixture into freezer containers and pour this mixture over cucumbers in container, enough to float the container of cucumbers.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Blend soup with 1/2 can water.

Measure out 1/4 cup of mixture and combine with beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, parsley and salt. Shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter. Brown in hot oil or Crisco, then add remaining soup mixture and relish.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes, stir occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: mom's pineapple-nut congealed salad
directions: Boil one cup water; dissolve jello and gelatine mixture into water and cool.
Add orange juice and pineapple juice.
Whip cream and fold in nuts, pineapple, carrots and mayonnaise.
Fold this into cooled jello mixture.
Place in mold and refrigerate. When mold begins to set, stir up to prevent the nuts and pineapple from sinking to the bottom.
When set, place in hot water and turn out immediately.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, water, oil, butter and 1/2 can condensed milk. Pour half of batter in a greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes or until done.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs (1 at a time), beating well after each egg.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Cut up apples and add to sugar mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Pour tomato sauce into a bowl.
Add spices, then add to macaroni.
Chop pepperoni into small pieces and add to mixture.
Put mixture into casserole; top with cheese mixture.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: hot clam spread
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and saute until brown.
Mix all ingredients together. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until real hot.

title: fresh strawberry chiffon dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.

title: chili mac
directions: In large skillet brushed with Wesson oil, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; pour off fat.
Add macaroni, kidney beans, Hunt's tomato sauce, water, chili powder and salt.
Cover and simmer gently for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese and heat until it melts.

title: tamale bake
directions: Drain tamales, reserving sauce.
Slice tamales crosswise; set aside.
In mixing bowl combine tamale sauce, flour, chili powder and garlic salt.
Add corn, eggs, olives and tamales.
Turn into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut into squares.
Serves 4.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Spread in pan, 9 x 13-inch, and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Boil the first nine ingredients for 20 minutes.
Stir often. Add next four ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: jam cake filling and icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, jam, raisins and coconut. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk which has soda in it.
Bake in 3 greased and floured layer cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool, fill and ice.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until you can just stick a fork in them. Do not overcook because they will be cooked again.
Run under cold water.
Peel and slice; they should make about 3 cups.
Place alternate layers of sweet potatoes and apples in buttered dish. Sprinkle each layer with sugar, salt, cinnamon and grated orange rind.
Dot top with butter.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for one hour.

title: stir-fry kielbasa stew
directions: In wok or skillet over medium-high heat, cook kielbasa about 2 minutes, stirring frequently, until lightly browned.
Stir in frozen vegetables, tomatoes, garlic and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes until vegetables are tender. Stir in beans and cook 1 to 2 minutes longer until heated through. Makes 4 servings.

title: scott's cheesy jalapeno dip
directions: If you have a food processor, combine all ingredients and process until smooth.
If not, place all in a mixing blender and blend until smooth.
Be patient, it will take a little time to become blended and you may have to scrape the sides of the blender several times to accomplish full blending.
Makes 2 1/4 cups. Serve with nacho chips.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salad oil, and salt and heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage, green pepper and onion mix. You can keep in a covered jar in refrigerator for as long as a week.

title: danish puff
directions: Cut flour and butter as for pie crust.
Add water.
Pat on cookie sheet.
Does not need to cover the whole sheet.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat milk; add butter and well beaten egg yolks.
Mix the sugar, cocoa, flour and pinch of salt together.
Stir into milk mixture and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Cool. Cover with meringue.
Brown in hot oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package and broccoli according to package, reserving some liquid from broccoli.
Mix together Rice-A-Roni, broccoli, chicken, soup, and grated cheese.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Add reserve liquid, if necessary.
Mix bread crumbs and margarine.
Top the casserole, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly. Serves 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Add the paste, sauce and seasonings to the meat.
Layer the noodles, meat, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Begin and end with the meat mixture. Bake for 45 minutes.
Let your lasagna stand for 15 minutes before cutting into 3-inch squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: french bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead the dough.
Allow to rise.
Knead again and make into loaves.
Make a slit into the center of each loaf, lengthwise.
Brush the loaves with melted butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine the remaining ingredients; blend and pour over top of cake mixture. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°. Cool and cut into squares.

title: kay's cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Put into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: light as a cloud dessert
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
Beat vanilla pudding mix and mix until smooth and thickened; stir in yogurt.
Layer 1/4 of the cake pieces, 1/2 can pie filling, 1/4 of the cake pieces and 1/2 of the vanilla pudding mixture in 3-quart glass serving bowl; repeat.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Refrigerate until chilled. Makes 12 servings, 280 calories, 350 mg. sodium, 1 mg. cholesterol, 1 g. saturated fat and 1 g. polyunsaturated fat. Calories can be reduced by using diet pudding.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Place over low heat until cheese and butter melt.
Thicken slightly with white sauce.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ye olde wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer at least 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix all soups, onions and Ro-Tel together.
In greased pan, layer chicken, Doritos and soup mixture, then top with cheese. Put in oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: sweet and sour meatball sauce
directions: Blend all the ingredients in blender. Make your favorite meatballs.
Brown in skillet.
Pour sauce over them.
Bake in oven at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: nut tree marshmallow dressing
directions: Boil together until it forms a thread.	Beat white of 3 eggs until stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites, beating continually. Add
vanilla
to taste.
When cool, add grated rind of orange and 1/3 cup mayonnaise.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir (not to burn); remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter, vanilla, oats and peanuts.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen clusters.

title: individual apple and walnut tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, combine butter and sugar and blend thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well.
Stir in flour and walnuts and blend well.
Divide batter among 6 buttered molds, patting each evenly over the bottom.
Peel and core apples; thinly slice.

Divide apple slices among tarts on top of batter. Place in preheated oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes until batter puffs slightly and the edges are golden. Sprinkle tarts with powdered sugar and return them to oven to brown slightly, about five minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and oil in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine sauerkraut, carrot, green pepper and onion in bowl.
Add liquid and blend thoroughly.
Cover and chill for 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Yields 4 cups.

title: herbed corn-on-the-cob
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix together butter, salt, pepper, parsley and rosemary. Spread about 1 tablespoon of butter mixture. Place corn in foil diagonally. Roll up tightly. Twist ends to seal in place on baking sheet. Bake for 30 minutes. When done, top remaining butter mixture on corn.

title: southern sugar pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl combine sugar, brown sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Blend well at medium speed.
Stir in margarine, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use as a dip for any of the following:
drained mandarin oranges, pineapple chunks, fresh pieces of bananas, apples, strawberries, cherries or fruit of your choice.

title: cinnamon triangles
directions: Remove pie crust from pan and roll flat.
Brush entire crust with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp.
Cut into triangles and serve.

title: eggplant and shrimp (or oysters)(servings:  6)
directions: Cut eggplant in large pieces after soaking in water to remove bitterness.
Mix with above ingredients in 3-inch deep baking dish.
Cover ingredients with more of the grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until hot completely through.
Oysters may be used instead of shrimp.

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 2 hours, covered.
Squeeze water out of cabbage.
Boil sugar, vinegar and water and cool.
Pour over cabbage and add remaining ingredients. Put in container with a lid.
This will keep well in a refrigerator for a long time.

title: butter supreme cake
directions: Mix together; put in Bundt pan and bake for 30 minutes at 375°, then 30 minutes at 325°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Cook macaroni in medium saucepan for 8 to 10 minutes or until almost tender, drain. Return macaroni to saucepan, add butter and stir until melted. Whisk together evaporated milk, eggs, mustard and pepper in medium bowl.
Add to macaroni mixture along with cheese; stir.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese begins to melt.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake for 10 minutes; stir.
Bake for an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and top is lightly golden.
Season with salt.

title: veal marsala
directions: Cut veal into 1 1/2 ounce scallopines flattened very thin. Sprinkle lightly with flour, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in large frying pan.
When hot, put in the scallopines and brown well on both sides over a fast heat.
When all are browned, add to the wine and cook one minute longer.
Arrange scallopines on platter.
Add stock or water to frying pan and with a spatula, loosen all particles stuck to the bottom and sides of the pan.
Pour over the meat.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Mix together broth, liquid smoke, vinegar and soy sauce. Place trimmed brisket in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour broth mixture over meat and cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours or until meat comes apart easily.
Slice beef across the grain in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Then crumble beef into a saucepan.
Add barbecue sauce and heat to boil.
Serve on rolls.
Makes 8 to 10 sandwiches.

title: pudding frosting
directions: Mix pudding, sugar and cold milk for 1 minute.
Let set for 1 minute. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 1/2 hour and spread on cake.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer 5 minutes.
Unroll dough; press onto bottom and sides of 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover crust with meat mixture.
Top with Velveeta.
Sprinkle sparingly with red pepper powder and crushed pepper.
Continue to bake until Velveeta melts. Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream.

title: lima beans in cream sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add lima beans and cream; stir often to prevent sticking or burning.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream cheese and margarine.
Add hot sauce and flour.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll in small balls, then flatten with fork.
Place in 375° oven.
Bake about 10 minutes or a little longer.

title: confetti candy
directions: Heat milk slowly in heavy pan, stirring constantly.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Prepare Pyrex dish with Pam spray and wax paper.
Pour candy mixture in pan.
Cut when cooled. (Do not set overnight before cutting.)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Add Cheez Whiz, soup, mushrooms, water chestnuts and almonds.
Spread in baking dish.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cotton soft italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1 1/2 cups warm water.
In a large pot or pan, make a well in the flour.
Add salt, oil, yeast, 2 or 3 cups warm water and sugar.
Mix well.
Do not make the dough too soft; sprinkle in more flour if necessary.
Cover with a tea towel.
Let rise for 1 to 2 hours, then mix again for 1 to 2 minutes.
After another hour, repeat 3 times.
One hour after the third mixing, make rolls or loaves using oil or shortening to coat dough all around.
Let rise for 3 hours.
Cook rolls for 20 minutes and loaves for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and bell pepper in oil until tender but not brown.
Add catsup, lemon peel, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Cook covered for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour over chicken in oblong pan and bake at 400° until tender, about 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Saute ground beef and garlic.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and chili
powder.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer one hour, stirring occasionally.
After one hour, add beans.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: double peanut fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and cook over medium heat stirring occasionally until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat add next 4 ingredients stir until mixture is well blended and fold in peanuts.
Pour into buttered 8 inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: baked sunshine pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, flavorings and carrots.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add to carrot mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Beat egg whites in bowl until stiff.
Fold into batter gently.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned.
Top warm pudding with Sunshine Sauce. Yield:
12 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients
and
bring
to a rolling boil. Chill. Line a baked
shell with strawberries, pour in mixture then top with Cool Whip.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll in small balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or to doneness desired.
Use spoon or two of water if too dry to mix well.
Do not crush corn flakes. Bake at 225° for 8 to 10 minutes for soft cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take meat from chicken and cut up the meat.
Mix all the ingredients together, except for placing crushed potato chips on top of casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: audrey's chicken
directions: Heat butter in large skillet.
Saute chicken and onions for 10 minutes. Add spices and tomatoes.
Place in baking dish.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a jelly roll pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese, salad dressing and Hidden Valley dry Ranch dressing.
Spread on cooled crescent sheet.
Add chopped vegetables such as:
peppers, tomatoes, carrots, celery, broccoli, cauliflower, olives, etc.
You could even add shrimp if desired.
Cut into 2 x 2 inch squares.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan; add broccoli. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: enchillas
directions: Boil chicken in salt and pepper and water for about 30 minutes. Take out; put in refrigerator.
Shred chicken into small pieces. Grate cheese.
Fry tortillas in pan with oil for about 2 seconds on both sides.
Place between paper towels.

title: tuna-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together. Next, add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each. Bake in a greased Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Remove from oven. Turn out on plate.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together peanuts, syrup and salt.
Cook 8 minutes on High, stirring after 4 minutes.
After cooking is complete, add oleo and vanilla.
Cook 1 minute longer on High.
Add baking soda and stir quickly until light and foamy. Immediately pour out onto lightly buttered baking sheet or piece of foil.
Spread thin.
Cool 1 hour.
Store in airtight container.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook shells partially for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Beat sugar with butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour alternately with milk and beat well.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan, and bake at 300° until cake tests done, about an hour and a half.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, oil and eggs together.
Add other ingredients. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chile verde(pork with green chiles)
directions: Brown meat slightly with garlic, onion, salt and pepper. Drain any grease off.
Add tomatoes, chiles and water.
Simmer 2 hours or until very tender.
Serve in flour tortillas with cooked rice.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix with hot water.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Mix beaten eggs and sugar well and then add to melted margarine, bringing to a boil.
Turn heat down and cook 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls when slightly cool.
Roll in coconut.
Enjoy!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and chopped onion together.
Drain well.
Add water, tomato paste, tomato sauce and mushrooms. Season to taste.
Let simmer on low for 15 minutes.
Boil spaghetti noodles in water until tender.
Mix all together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mayonnaise biscuits #1
directions: Mix ingredients and drop spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: dill cucumber salad
directions: Mix sour cream, vinegar, sugar, dill, salt and pepper. Gently toss in cucumbers and onions; stir gently. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheese logs(good for christmas time)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May have to mix with hands. Form into 10 or 12 rolls by rolling mixture between hands, then roll in pecan pieces that have been poured into a plate.
Place each roll into a Baggies and freeze until needed.
Take out of freezer about an hour before needed.
Serve with crackers.
Rolls are about 6 inches long.

title: preserved plums or plum sauce
directions: Boil plums 15 minutes. Drain off juice. Add all other ingredients and boil 30 minutes.
Pour into Mason jars while still very hot so jars will seal.

title: choco peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients of oats, flour and baking soda.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: dill casserole bread
directions: Generously grease 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, sugar, onion, dill seed, salt, baking soda and yeast; blend well.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned fruit well, reserving only pineapple juice. I like to rinse the cherries well, otherwise they tend to bleed and turn the fruit salad pink. Slice bananas into extra large bowl with pineapple juice. Make sure banana slices are coated well with juice so they do not turn dark. Drain juice. Cut peaches and mandarin oranges into smaller bite size pieces. Add to bananas. Slice cherries in half and add to fruit. Add remaining ingredients and stir gently until mixed well. Keep refrigerated.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cranberry jelly and lemon juice.
Put in mold and freeze. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour on top of mold and refreeze.

title: "spoon" bread
directions: Put corn meal and butter in a mixing bowl.
Add boiling water. Stir until moistened.
Beat in egg and milk.
Combine baking powder, salt, flour and sugar.
Beat into batter.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 450° for about 30 minutes or until set and browned.

title: almeta's fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add chopped apples.
Sift together
flour,
baking
soda,
cinnamon,	salt and apple pie spice.
Add
to
mixture
and
mix thoroughly.
This will be a thick batter.
Add	nuts and mix again.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until done, about an hour.

title: lo-cal banana heaven
directions: In a deep cake pan, completely cover the bottom with one layer of vanilla wafers and put aside.
In a bowl, mix one box of pudding up.
Pour on top of cookie layer, then mix other box of pudding and squash up bananas in it.
Pour on top of layer of regular pudding.
Top with Cool Whip lite and enjoy.
You don't have to feel guilty a bit!

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower.
Add cheese and onion.
Store in airtight container.
Mix and refrigerate overnight the Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.

title: roasted cornish hens with coriander glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove giblets from hens.
Rinse and pat hens dry.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender. Drain.
In saucepan, melt butter, then blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk. Cook and stir until thick. Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in macaroni.
Turn into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: carol's chocolate pies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.
